Commentary: Oh..how close is this! Tim Southee starts with a good-length delivery, on middle, shaping in, Zak Crawley misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW, but turned down as in real time it looks like going down the leg side.
Back of a length and on off, Zak Crawley looks to play at it, but gets a leading edge towards fourth slip.
This is on a hard length and outside off, shaping further away, Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Length again, outside off again, Zak Crawley decides not to play at it again.
Tim Southee continues with the good length, on off, Zak Crawley guides it with the outer half towards gully.
Tim Southee starts with a maiden over! He goes a bit fuller this time, on off, shaping away, Zak Crawley lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
England are Ben Duckett are underway now! Matt Henry begins with a full delivery but down the leg side, Ben Duckett flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Pulls his length back a bit, on the fifth stump line, Ben Duckett leaves it alone.

BEAUTY! Matt Henry serves this on a good length and on middle, swinging away with some extra bounce, Ben Duckett gets cut in half and the ball goes just past his bat and off his thighs towards the keeper. There is an appela for the caught behind, but turned down. New Zealand reviews it but loses it as UltraEdge shows no bat involved.
Fuller one and on off, Ben Duckett drives it down the pitch.
Back of a length and on leg, angling in, Ben Duckett nudges it through backward square leg for a single.
Full again and on off, Zak Crawley drives it uppishly but wide of the bowler and the fielder at short covers fumbles a bit which allows another run.
Fuller in length and around leg, Zak Crawley tickles it towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a good length and on off, angling in, Ben Duckett turns it towards square leg.
A bit slower this time, on a length again and on middle, Ben Duckett knocks it towards square leg once more.
Tim Southee pitches this one up, outside off, Ben Duckett tries to drive it away from his body, but mistimes it onto the pitch.
Full and on middle, Ben Duckett pushes it towards short covers.
Pulls his length back, on off, Ben Duckett leans on and blocks it out down the pitch.
Good leave! Matt Henry bowls this on a hard length and around off, shaping away, Zak Crawley thinks about playing it, but withdraws his bat in the end.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Zak Crawley defends it to the left of the bowler.
This is on a good length and on the sixth stump line, swinging in, Zak Crawley lets it go to the keeper.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Matt Henry draws first blood! Zak Crawley goes for another disappointing score. Matt Henry serves this on a hard length and on off, nips away a bit after hitting the deck, Zak Crawley tries to block it out, but that little away movement takes a thin edge of his bat towards the keeper where Tom Blundell makes no mistake. An early blow for England.
Howout: c Tom Blundell b Matt Henry

Commentary: A bit fuller and on off, angling in, Ollie Pope uses his feet and tries to flick it away, but misses and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Ollie Pope gets off the mark in style! Matt Henry pitches this one up, on middle, Ollie Pope comes forward again, but times his flick perfectly towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.

Another appeal for LBW, but turned down again. Tim Southee comes around the wicket and bowls this on a good length, on middle, angling in, Ben Duckett misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. The Kiwis appeal, but the it looks like it is going over the stumps.
Length again and on middle, Ben Duckett looks to work it away, but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Touch fuller and on off, Ben Duckett moves across and keeps it to the leg side.
Fuller again and around off, Ben Duckett goes for the big drive, but gets another inside edge towards square leg.

Overpitched and outside off, Ben Duckett closes his face of the bat early while trying to flick, and gets a top edge over backward point. Two runs taken. Tim Southee is asking a lot of questions here.
This is pitched up and on off, Ben Duckett drives it towards the bowler where Tim Southee goes down and gets a hand to it as Kane Williamson from mid off mops it up. They cross.
Fuller one and just around leg, Ben Duckett clips it towards deep square leg where Neil Wagner chases it down and slides to keep it in. Three runs taken!
Full again and on middel, Ollie Pope works it wide of square leg and comes back for the second.
Overpitched and on middle, Ollie Pope mistimes his drive towards mid on.
FOUR! Fine shot! Matt Henry serves this full again but around off this time, Ollie Pope takes a couple of steps forward and drives it beautifully wide of mid off for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN AT SLIPS! Matt Henry strikes again! This time he gets Ollie Pope who was looking in good touch. New Zealand set up the batter here. They pushed the deep square leg fielder back on the previous ball which put a doubt in the mind of Pope as he is expecting a short ball, but Matt Henry decides to bowl this on a good length and on off, straightens after hitting the deck, Ollie Pope tries to work it away with no footwork and gets a thick outside edge towards third slip where Michael Bracewell takes a sharp catch to his left.
Howout: c Michael Bracewell b Matt Henry

Commentary: A huge shout for LBW, but the finger stays down again. However, New Zealand takes another review. Matt Henry serves this full and on off, shaping in, Joe Root uses his feet to flick it away, but misses and gets hit on the pads. UltraEdge shows no bat involved and Ball Tracking indicates that impact is umpire's call and wickets is missing. So, the Kiwis lose another review.
This is full and on off, Ben Duckett works it with the inner half towards square leg.
On a length and on off, Ben Duckett blocks it out.
Back of a length and on off, Ben Duckett bunts it towards point.

OUT! TAKEN! Is it a plane? Is it a bird? No, it is a flying Michael Bracewell to take an absolute stunner. New Zealand are on fire here. Tim Southee lands this on a hard length and outside off, Ben Duckett moves across and tries to defend, but the movement away takes an outside edge as the ball flies to left of thrid slip where Michael Bracewell dives to that side and takes a one-handed stunner with his left hand. It bobbled, but he did well to hang on. England three down now!
Howout: c Michael Bracewell b Tim Southee

Commentary: Southee goes full and on off. Brook defends it into the deck with hard hands.
Good running! It is full, and on off. Brook skips down the track and wrists it nicely through mid-wicket. They take three runs.
This is on a good length and on off, Harry Brook leaves it alone.
Length again and on middle, angling in, Harry Brook misses his flick and the ball lobs up off his pads to the leg side.

EDGED AND FOUR! Matt Henry lands this on a hard length and on off, Harry Brook looks to defend, but gets opened up and the ball takes the outside edge. However, it goes between third slip and the gully fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook steers it towrds gully.
Fuller one and on middle, Harry Brook blocks it down the pitch.
Short of a length and on middle, Harry Brook defends it off the back foot this time.
Full and on middle, Joe Root stays there and knocks it back towards the bowler.
Back of a length and on leg, Joe Root nudges it towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Nice shot! Tim Southee serves this full and on off, Harry Brook shows the full face of the bat and drives it firmly past cover-point for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! Tim Southee lands this short and wide of off pole, Harry Brook frees his arms and cuts it through point for another boundary.

FOUR! Harry Brook is taking on Tim Southee here! This is pitched and outside off again, Harry Brook skips down the track and slashes hard at it, and the ball goes over point for the third boundary of the player. The 'Bazball' approach continues from England.
Fuller one and on off, Harry Brook leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on off, Joe Root blocks it out.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Joe Root leans on and knocks it down the pitch.
Full again and on middle, Joe Root tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Through the gap! Joe Root gets his first boundary now. This is pitched up and outside off, Joe Root goes for the drive, but gets a thick outside edge between point and gully for four more runs.
BEAUTY! Matt Henry lands this on a good length, on middle, nips away a bit, Joe Root is stuck in his creass and the ball just goes past the outside edge towards the keeper.
Length again and on off, Joe Root looks to defend, but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball rolls towards short covers. They cross.
A length ball, in the channel. Joe Root shuffles across but does not go through with his shot.
Much fuller, on fourth stump, swinging away. Joe Root steps across and blocks it out.
Joe Root now comes down the wicket and defends this full one.
Good length, around off. Joe Root stands way outside the crease, uses his feet once again and dabs it in front of the bowler.
A loud appeal for lbw but turned down! It is a length ball, that nips in a touch from outside off. Joe Root gets a thick inside edge on to his pads.
Goes full and on off. Root comes down the track and blocks this watchfully. A maiden for Daryl Mitchell to start with.
Matt Henry fires it full and on off. Harry Brook gets a thick inside edge on it. He gets lucky here to not see the ball go on to crash into his stumps.
Matt Henry now bends his back hard. This one flies off the deck. This one catches Harry Brook by surprise. He gets it towards gully off the outer half. Does not carry though.
A length ball, drifting down leg. Harry Brook tries to clip it away but it dies on the leg side off his pads.
FOUR LEG BYES! It is a bit short, drifitng down leg. Harry Brook is unable to glance it around the corner. It brushes high thigh pad and runs down to fine leg.
On off, defended out.
Matt Henry fires in a yorker-length delivery, around off. Harry Brook jams it out towards mid off. A probing over from Henry comes to an end.
Short and outside off. Joe Root cuts it to the left of sweeper cover and gets a single.
A bit fuller, outside off. This one gets some extra bounce. Tom Blundell only gets a hand on it as he is standing close to the stumps.
Back of a length, outside off. Harry Brook cuts it hard to sweeper cover for a single.
Length, outside off, shaping further away. Joe Root lets it be.
Full and on off. Root taps it to cover and crosses.
Length, on top of off. Brook stays back and defends it watchfully.
Matt Henry dishes a length ball, on off. Joe Root defends it out solidly off the back foot.
Full, on middle and leg. Root nudges it to the leg side.
Goes full, outside off, shaping away. Joe Root leaves it alone for the keeper.
Joe Root stands way outside the crease. Matt Henry serves it full, wide of off. Root shoulders his arms at it.
A length ball, on off, Root blocks it back to the bowler.
Joe Root presses forward to this full ball and dabs it out to cover for a quick single.
Short and wide. Root frees his arms and cuts it hard. There is protection in the deep. Only one taken.
A half-volley, outside off. Brook leans in and pushes it through point for a single.
Short one, outside off. Root leans back and cuts it past backward point. Devon Conway runs to his left and keeps it down to a single.
FOUR! Solid shot. It is overpitched, on fourth stump. Harry Brook goes back and lofts it over the bowler's head for a cracking boundary.
Length and on off, steered into the slip cordon.
On a length, on fourth stump. Harry Brook fends it down to the right of gully.
Tim Southee dishes a length ball, wide of away, moving further away. Joe Root lets it be.
A length ball, sliding down leg. Joe Root comes down the track and makes the leave.
Full length, wide of off. Left alone.
On off, blocked out to extra cover.
Joe Root charges down the track to this good-length delivery and defends it away.
On a length, around off. Root stays back and defends ot back to the bowler.
Too full and straight, on the pads. Harry Brook flicks it to deep square leg and gets to the other end.
Full again, angled into the pads. Root clips it to deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Joe Root comes down the track to this full one and checks his drive here. Michael Bracewell dives to his right at short cover and makes a sharp stop.
Full and on off, blocked to covers watchfully.
A single now as this is flicked to the leg side.
Length, outside off, left alone by Brook.
Short ball, on off. Joe Root rides the bounce and pulls it to deep square leg, but only for a single.
Harry Brook presses forward and defends this length ball watchfully.
Back of a length, outside off. Harry Brook chops it towards mid off. One taken.
Full, on fifth stump. Root steps across and defends it to backward point.
Good length, outside off. Joe Root comes down the track and dabs it out.
A length ball, angled in on middle. Root defends it out with a straight bat.
Full, wide of off. Brook slashes it into covers.
A bit short, outside off. Brook guides it past gully and crosses.
Much fuller, on off. Joe Root drives it gently down the park towards mid off. One taken.
WIDE! A sharp bumper, on off. This one flies over the batter's head. The umpire signals a wide.
Neil Wagner serves it full, outside off, angling across the right-hander. Left alone.

It is a short ball, on middle. Harry Brook hangs back and tries to pull it away. The ball takes the outside edge and lobs to the right of mid on. Tim Southee is unable to get there in time. One taken.
LEG BYE! It is full, sliding down leg. Joe Root misses his flick. The ball rolls out off his pads and they collect a leg bye.
Length, in the channel. Left alone.
A single now as this short one is pulled to deep mid-wicket.
Length, outside off, tapped to point.
It is full and on off. Brook gets it to mid-wicket off the inner half and crosses.
Much fuller, on off. Joe Root flicks it past mid on. The batters cross for two runs.
Length and on off, defended out.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Brook! Neil Wagner serves a half-volley, on the leg stump line, Harry Brook stays there and clips it towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
This is on a good length and on off, Harry Brook bunts it onto the ground towards gully who parries it towards deep point while trying to stop it. A single is taken.
A bit fuller and on off, Joe Root taps it towards cover-point for a run.
Sharp bowling! Neil Wagner bangs in a fiery bouncer, on middle, Harry Brook goes for the pull shot, but is a bit late and misses it.
FOUR! Another boundary for Brook! Neil Wagner tries another bouncer, but this on just sits up nicely for the batter, on off, Harry Brook swivels and pulls it through mid-wicket for four more runs.
Neil Wagner gets the bouncer right this time around leg, Harry Brook misses his pull and the ball just goes past his gloves to the keeper.
On a length and on off, Joe Root steers it towards gully.
BEATEN! Tim Southee bowls this on a hard length and on middle, draws the batter forward and nips away a bit too, Joe Root gets opened up the ball goes past the outside edge as he tries to play it.
Length again and on off, Joe Root pushes it towards covers.
Goes a bit fuller and on middle, Joe Root looks to flick, but closes the face of the bat early and gets a leading edge towards short mid off.
Fuller again and on middle, Joe Root tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off, Joe Root stays back and knocks it towards short covers. A maiden over for Tim Southee!
Fuller one and on middle, Harry Brook blocks it to the off side.
Full again and on off, Harry Brook drives it towards mid off.
Neil Wagner pitches it up, on off, Harry Brook forces it towards mid on. He is losing his patience a bit.
FOUR! Harry Brook breaks the shackles! Neil Wagner serves this full once again and on leg, Harry Brook makes some room and lofts it over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Another overpithched delivery, on off, Harry Brook smacks it on the bounce towards mid off.
Back of a length and outside off, Harry Brook chops it out towards point.
Fuller in length and on off, Joe Root keeps it out to the off side.
Full again and on middle, angling in, Joe Root works it towards the left of short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Joe Root guides it towards gully.
Goes back to his fuller length and around off, Joe Root moves across and tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
This is on a good length and on off, angling in, Joe Root lets it go to the keeper.
Pitched up, on middle, Joe Root flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Joe Root blocks it out solidly.
On a length and on off, Joe Root taps it wide of short covers and scampers across for a single.
Length again and on middle, Harry Brook defends it back to the bowler.
Neil Wagner tests Harry Brook with another sharp bouncer, on leg, Brook ducks under it.
Goes full and on off, Harry Brook knocks it towards point.
FOUR! Powerful shot! Neil Wagner lands this short and on middle, Harry Brook is ready for it this time and hammers it wide of deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Michael Bracewell starts with a short delivery, on leg, turning in, Joe Root leaves it alone as Tom Blundell collects it behind the stumps.
Floated, short and on middle, Joe Root blocks it down the pitch.
Tossed up, full and on off, Joe Root defends it on the front foot.
A bit short and on middle, Joe Root moves back and works it towards square leg for a run.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR BROOK! This has been another fine knock from him and this is fifth fifty plus score in a row. He will look to make this one big now. Coming to the delivery, Michael Bracewell flights this up, full and on off, Harry Brook gets his front foot towards the ball and drills ti through cover-point. It slows down a bit and the fieder chases it and slides to stop it, but his fingers touches the ropes as he tries to push the ball back in. After a few replays, the umpire signals a boundary. 100 up for England!
A dot to end the over! Michael Bracewell angles this one into the batter, on leg, Harry Brook moves back and punches it towards cover-point. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Tim Southee begins with a hard-length delivery outside off, shaping further away, Joe Root leaves it alone.
Goes fuller this time, on middle, Joe Root tucks it wide of short mid on where the fielder dives to his right to stop it. They cross.
Back of a length and around off, Harry Brook offers not shot at it.
This is pitched up and outside off, Harry Brook drills it wide deep point for a brace.
Fullish one and on off, shaping away, Harry Brook lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
Length and on off, Harry Brook keeps it out to the off side.
This is on a good length and on off, Joe Root works it with the outer half towards covers for a single.
Goes fuller and on middle, Harry Brook blocks it down the pitch.
Fuller again and on off, Harry Brook taps it in front of short covers for a quick run.
Good running! Matt Henry bowls this back of a length and on off, Joe Root dabs it wide of short covers again for one more.
Overpitched and on middle, Harry Brook drills it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and on middle, angling in, Harry Brook looks to play at it, but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball goes nowhere.
Full and on middle, Joe Root defends it down the pitch.
On a length and middle, Joe Root is solid in his defense again.
A bit fuller and on off, Joe Root keeps it out to the off side.
On middle, blocked out.
Back of a length and on off, Joe Root cuts it towards gully.
Another maiden for Tim Southee! He serves this full and on off, Joe Root drives it straight to mid off. The scoring rate has slowed down a bit after Lunch.
This is on a hard length and on off, Harry Brook defends it towards point.
Full and on off, Harry Brook drives it firmly to the left of the bowler where Matt Henry goes down and makes a hafl-stop.
This is on a good length and on off, Harry Brook tries to block it with soft hands, but gets an outside edge and the ball goes on the bounce towards slip cordon.
Pitched up, on middle, Harry Brook knocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Matt Henry bowls this full again and on off, Harry Brook stays there and shows the full face of the bat to drive it well past mid off for a boundary.
Good comeback from Henry! He lands this on a good length and on middle, nips away, Harry Brook looks to play at it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller in length and on off, Joe Root guides it towards gully where the fielder dives to his left ot stop it.
On a length and on off, Joe Root uses his feet and keeps it out to the off side.
This is full and around off, Joe Root drives it firmly but finds short covers.
Back of a length and on off, Joe Root backs away, but cuts it straight to gully.
Touch fuller and around off, shaping away, Joe Root offers no shot at it.
Fuller again and on off too, Joe Root decides to leave it alone.
This is on a good length and on off, shaping away, Harry Brook pats it down towards gully.
Full and on middle, Harry Brook blocks it out.
Full again and on middle, Harry Brook miscues his drive back towards the bowler where Matt Henry picks it up and thorws at the batter's end to show some aggression.
Matt Henry continues with the fuller length but down the leg side this time, Harry Brook misses his flick and Tom Blundell collects it well diving to his left behind the stumps.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook dabs it down towards point.

Matt Henry is causing some trouble to Brook here. He lands this on a hard length and on off, shaping away, Harry Brook once again gets cut in half and knocks it with the outer half towards short covers.
Fuller in length and on middle, Joe Root clips it towards wide of deep square leg for a couple of runs.
This is on a good lengt and on leg, Joe Root misses his flick as the ball goes off his pads towards square leg. A leg bye is taken.
Back of a length and outside off, Harry Brook cuts it towards deep point for a run.
Overpitched and on off, Joe Root drills it wide of covers where Michael Bracewell dives to his right to make a good stop. They cross.
Short of a length and on off, Harry Brook dabs it towards gully.

Oh..that is close! Daryl Mitchell serves this full and on off, Harry Brook goes for the big booming drive on the up, but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball just goes past the stumps towards fine leg. Two runs taken!
Full and on middle, Joe Root works it off the inner half towards mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook punches it through covers for a brace. With that, the 100-run partnership comes up between these two batters.
This is on a hard length and on middle, angling in, Harry Brook looks to play at it, but misse and gets hit on his back elbow. That is going to hurt.
Matt Henry bangs in a bouncer, on middle and leg, Harry Brook ducks under it.
Short again and on middle, Harry Brook gets hurried and awkwardly keeps it out towards the short leg region. Tim Southee should be lookiing to put a short leg now.
Fuller one and on off, Harry Brook defends it on the front foot.
This is pitched up, on off, Joe Root drives it towards mid off.
On a length and on middle, Joe Root nudges it to the right of square leg for a quick single.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook steers it towards gully.
SIX! BANG! Harry Brook goes big now! Daryl Mitchell serves this full and on off, in the slot, Harry Brook stays there and smokes it over the long off fence for a biggie.
SIX! Harry Brook is making his intentions clear here! This is full again and on middle, Harry Brook this time uses his bottom hand and slogs it over the long on fence for a maximum.
On a length and on middle, Harry Brook turns it to the leg side. 13 runs off the over then!

A huge shout for LBW, but turned down. Matt Henry convinces Tim Southee to go for the review. Henry serves this full and on middle, angling in, Joe Root misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. UltrEdge shows no bat involved and Balll Tracking indicates that wickets is umpire's call. New Zealand keep their review though.
Full again and on middle, Joe Root uses his feet and clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
On a length and on leg, Harry Brook gets hurried and nudges it towards square leg for a run.
Back of a length and around leg, Joe Root misses his flick as the ball deflects off his pads towards square leg. A leg bye is taken.
This is on a hard length and down the leg, Harry Brook tickles it towards fine leg for one.
Overpitched and on the pads, Joe Root tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Harry Brook rocks back to this short one and slaps it towards sweeper cover for a brace.
Length, on the pads. Brook tucks it to deep square and crosses.
Length, on fourth stump. Root gets behind and defends it out.
Joe Root lunges to this full ball and dabs it out.
Joe Root now uses his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball, clips it towards mid on and takes a single.
Short one, wide of off. Harry Brook slashes it to deep point for a single.
Length, angled into the pads. Brook stays back and nudges it to mid-wicket for one.
Shorter, on middle and leg. Root swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side only for a single.
Good length, in the channel, blocked out to point.
FOUR! What a shot! So pleasing to the eyes as well. It is pitched up, on off. Brook stands tall and lofts it firmly over the bowler's head. A couple of bounces over the ropes.
Fraction short, on off. Brook slaps it hard but only in direction of the bowler. Matt Henry does well to kill the pace of it.
A length ball, angled into the pads. Brook stays back and tries to flick it away but misses.
Flatter, on leg. Root goes back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single. 150 is up for England now.
FOUR! Too easy for Brook, with the form that he is in. It is a half-volley, on fourth stump. Harry Brook creams it through covers off the front foot for four runs.
A single now as this is pushed to the off side.
Loops it up, around middle. Joe Root flicks it to mid on.
On middle and leg, tucked to short mid-wicket.
Fuller and on off. Root lunges forward, closes the face and works it to square leg. They take a single.
Wagner goes full, angling across, around off. Root comes down and miscues it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Incredible stroke. It is very full, angling across, wide of off. Joe Root prods and drives it through cover for a fine boundary.
Length and on off. Root dabs it towards backward point and gets to the other end safely.
Harry Brook cuts this short one to sweeper cover for one.
It is full and on the pads. Joe Root flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.

Full length, outside off. Harry Brook leans in and drives it through the gap between mid off and extra cover. Tim Southee gives it a chase and keeps it down to three runs. Harry Brook moves to 95 runs off just 98 balls.
Tossed up, full and on off, Harry Brook drives it towards short covers.
Floated, short and on middle, turning in, Harry Brook works it with the inner half towards square leg for a single.
Flighted, full and on off, Joe Root leans on and blocks it out.
Floats it up, full and on off. Root drives it back to the bowler.
Loops it up, full and on off. It dips as well. Joe Root is quick to jam it out with his bat.
Goes full, on middle and leg. Joe Root prods and nudges it to the leg side.
Length, in the channel. Brook dabs it to backward point.
Harry Brook swivels on his back foot and pulls this short one to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full length, angled across, outside off. Root does not go after it.
Fuller, wide of off. Joe Root leans in and drives it through covers for one more.
Wagner goes full again, wide of off. Harry Brook slashes hard but only connects with thin air.
Good length, on fifth stump. Brook hangs back and punches it towards sweeper cover, for one more.
A bit short, outside off. Brook slaps it hard to the off side, could not penetrate the gap though.
Short and on off. Harry Brook goes back and punches it through the line to covers. He takes a single and moves to 99. This single also brings up a 150-run stand between these two.
Darted on the pads, nudged to short leg.
Much fuller, on middle and leg. Joe Root tucks it to short leg.
Floats it up, around middle. It turns down leg with some extra bounce. Root fails to tickle it away.
Full and outside off. Root leans in and dabs it to cover for a single.
Fuller, on leg. Joe Root uses his feet and wrists it towards cow corner. The batters take two runs and Harry Brook needs to wait some more for his ton here.
Good length, outside off. It flies off the deck. Tom Blundell gathers it at a good height as Joe Root makes the leave.
On a length, on fourth stump. Root shuffles and dabs it towards point.
Wagner goes full and on off. Joe Root works it towards mid on.
Joe Root stays back to this full ball and clips it to deep square leg. The batters take two runs with ease.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Joe Root pulls it to deep square leg and retains the strike. He moves to 49 now.
Tossed up, around off, it turns in off the deck. Root tucks it to the right of short leg.
Once again fires on to the pads. Joe Root clips it to short leg.
It is quicker and flatter, on off. Joe Root goes back and punches it to point for a single. A half-century for Joe Root. He has certainly taken his side out of trouble here with his knock.

FOUR! Harry Brook gets his TON in style. His fourth Test century in his last 5 matches. This is some start to his Test career. Short ball, outside off. Harry Brook cuts it past point and it races away. Harry Brook receives a standing ovation here for his sublime knock.
On leg, flicked to the leg side.
Looped up, on middle and leg, clipped to short mid-wicket.
Good length, outside off. Joe Root shuffles and fends it to backward point.
Joe Root comes down the track to this length ball and flicks it to deep mid-wicket. One taken.
Full length, on fourth stump. Brook lunges and blocks it away.
Harry Brook gets on his front foot and drives this full ball to covers.
Short one, outside off. Brook cuts it to deep point and crosses.
A single to end the over! Too full and straight, on the pads. Joe Root flicks it through square leg and gets a single.
Fuller one and on off, Joe Root knocks it wide of short covers. He wants the run, but he is sent back.
Full again and on off, Joe Root pushes it through cover-point for a single.
Goes short and on middle, Harry Brook pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Pitched up, on off, Joe Root drills it towards deep point for one.
Short and on middle, Harry Brook measures his pull shot well towards deep square leg again for one more.
FOUR! Classic Root! Neil Wagner serves this full and around off, Joe Root takes hs front foot near the ball and drives it sweetly through covers for a boundary.
EDGED AND FOUR! Tim Southee bowls this on a good length and on off, Harry Brook lookst to block it, but gets an inside edge just past the stumps towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook bunts it towards second slip.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook taps it towards gully.
Tim Southee pitches it up, on off, Harry Brook pushes it towards deep backward point for a single.
Fullish and on middle, Joe Root clips it through square leg for one.
Short and on middle, Harry Brook pulls it on the bounce towards deep mid-wicket for a run. 200 up for England!
FOUR! Powered away! Neil Wagner lands this short of a length and on leg, Harry Brook backs away and swats it towards the long on fence for a boundary.

Short of a length again and outside off, Harry Brook makes room and flat-bats it down the pitch where Joe Root shows quick reflexes to spread his legs and the ball goes between them towards the long off region. They cross.
Short delivery, on middle, Joe Root swivels and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a brace.
Neil Wagner continues with the shorter length, on leg this time, Joe Root pulls it straight to square leg.
Another short delivery around leg, Joe Root finds backward square leg again with his pull shot.

FOUR! Joe Root finds the gap this time! Neil Wagner bangs this short again, on middle, Joe Root hammers it wide of deep square leg where the fielder is a bit late to react and the ball goes over the fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off, Harry Brook guides it through point for a single.
A bit fuller and on off, Joe Root knocks it towards short covers.
On a length and on off, Joe Root uses his feet and taps it in front of short covers for a quick run.

FOUR! Brilliant timing! Tim Southee serves this touch fuller and outside off, Harry Brook punches it firmly wide of sweeper covers where Will Young covers his ground and dives to his right, but fails to stop it from going for a boundary.
Short and on middle, Harry Brook pulls it towards deep backward square leg for one.
This is on a good length and on off, Joe Root pushes it towards gully.
Short and outside off, Harry Brook slaps it towards long off where Kane Williamson comes in from long on and slides in to stop it. They cross.
On a length and on off, Joe Root makes room and cuts it towards extra covers where the fielder misfields and allows the second run. 200-run partnership comes up with that between these two batters.
Short delivery, on middle, Joe Root pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
Another short delivery, on leg, Harry Brook hooks it past the diving backward square leg fielder for one.
Back of a length and on middle, Joe Root swivels and pulls it towards deep sqaure leg for one more.
Neil Wagner sees the batter back away and serves this full and outside off, Harry Brook is too far away from the ball and decides to leave it alone.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Joe Root leans on and turns it to the leg side.
Floated, full and on off, Joe Root pushes it towards point.
Flighted, full and on middle, Joe Root defends it on the front foot.
Flatter, full and on middle, Joe Root goes down, takes it on the full and paddle-sweeps it wide of fine leg where the fielder dives to his right to stop it. Two runs taken!
Slower through the air, on off, Joe Root knocks it towards covers.
Short and on off, Joe Root moves back and punches it towards covers.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Neil Wagner bowls this on a hard length and slighlty outside off, Harry Brook frees his arms and cuts it wide of deep point for a boundary.
SIX! BOOM! Harry Brook is showing no signs of stopping here. This is full and on middle, Harry Brook clears his front leg and smacks it over the wide long on fence for a biggie.
On a length and on leg, Harry Brook nudges it towards backward square leg.
Short and on middle, Harry Brook pulls it towards deep square leg for a run.
This is on a good length and on off, Joe Root steers it towards gully.
Back of a length and on off, Joe Root keeps it out towards gully. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
This is on a good length and on leg, Harry Brook flicks it through square leg for a single.
Length again and on middle, Joe Root tucks it to the right of short mid-wicket for a run.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook guides it towards gully.
Goes fuller this time, on leg, Harry Brook is early into his drive and mistimes it towards mid on.
FOUR! Elegant from brook! Matt Henry serves this full and on off, Harry Brook stays there and drills it past mid off for a boundary.
Fuller and on off, Harry Brook taps it wide of short covers for a quick single.
Fuller one and on off, Harry Brook miscues his drive towards mid off.
Full again and on middle, angling in, Harry Brook blocks it down the pitch.
Another full delivery, on off, Harry Brook drives it straight to mid off.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook dabs it towards gully.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook punches it wide of deep point for a brace.
Full and on middle, Harry Brook blocks it out to the leg side.
On a length and on middle, Joe Root tucks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook punches it through covers for a run.
Short of a length and around leg, Joe Root nudges it towards fine leg for one.

FOUR! Harry Brook finds the fence again! Matt Henry lands this short and on off, Harry Brook picks up the length early and pulls it in front of square on the leg side for a boundary. 250 up for England!

FOUR! Deft touch! 150 up for Brook! This is on a good length and on off, Harry Brook waits for it and late cuts it between third slip and gully for a boundary. This has been a superb effort from him and he will be eying that double ton now.
Good comeback from Henry! He bowls this on a hard length and on off, angling in, Harry Brook gets cut in half and misses it while trying to fend it away.
Full and on middle, Joe Root tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, Joe Root guides it towards gully.
Pitched up, on middle, Joe Root drills it back towards the bowler where Neil Wagner goes dwon and makes a good stop.
Just short! This is full again and on middle, Joe Root is early into his drive and plays it uppishly towards the bowler where it just falls short of Neil Wagner.
On a length and on middle, Joe Root works it towards short mid-wicket.
Goes fuller and on off, Joe Root knocks it towards gully.
This is full and on off, swinging in, Harry Brook blocks it towards short covers.
Full again and on off, Harry Brook goes down and tries to paddle it, but hits it onto his pads as the ball goes nowhere.
Pitched up, on middle, Harry Brook drives it down the pitch and the ball hits the stumps at the bowler's end.

SIX! Up, up and away! Daryl Mitchell continues to bowl fuller, on off, Harry Brook stays there and dispatches it over the long on fence for a biggie. He moves to 159 and this becomes his highest score in Test cricket.
Daryl Mitchell sees the batter advance and serves this full and outside off, Harry Brook reaches for it, and forces it towards extra covers with no timing.
FOUR! Great shot! This is another full delivery, on off, Harry Brook drives it past the diving bowler and wide of mid off for a boundary. He holds the pose for a few seconds after playing that shot.
Goes full and on fourth stump. Joe Root gets on his front foot and gets it towards mid on off the outer half.
Very full, in the blockhole. Root jams it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on leg stump. Joe Root nudges it towards mid on.
Length and on off, pushed to the off side.
Wagner goes full, wide of off. Joe Root plays it late and steers it down to third man for a brace.
A dot to end the over! It is pitched up, outside off. Joe Root pushes it gently towards extra cover.
FOUR! Smacked! It is full, wide outside off. Harry Brook slashes hard through the line and it races away to the fence through the cover region.
Short, outside off. Harry Brook cuts it to deep point and crosses.
Joe Root now hangs back to this length ball and cuts it with control towards sweeper cover. They take one.
Short again, wide of off. Brook goes back and cuts it through covers for another single.
Another single as Joe Root dabs this short one past backward point.
Goes full, in the channel. Harry Brook drives it gently towards mid off. The stand between these two moves to 257 runs.
FOUR! Powerfully hit! It is tossed up, full and on off. Harry Brook uses his feet and lofts it over mid off for a cracking boundary.
Full and on middle. Harry Brook miscues it to long and gets to the other end.
Full and on off. Root prods and taps it to cover for a quick single.
Another single now as this is tucked towards mid on.
A bit short, on off. Root punches it towards deep point and collects three runs before the fielder cuts it out.
Fuller and on off. Brook works it to mid on and crosses for one.
Daryl Mitchell serves a length ball, angled into the pads. Harry Brook stays back and nudges it to mid-wicket.
SIX! Woah! This is just brutal from Brook. Mitchell goes full and on off. Harry Brook shuffles across and scoops it over the keeper's head for a biggie.
Length and on middle. Brook stays back and defends it to the leg side.
It is full and on off. Harry Brook closes the face and works it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Full length and on off. Root drives it back to the bowler. Daryl Mitchell uses his right boot to stop the ball.
A single now as this full one is flicked past mid on by Root.
It is full, angled in around off. Root eases it to mid off.
FOUR! Down the ground! It is pitched up, on off. Joe Root uses his feet and smacks it down the ground. It goes past the bowler and down to the long off fence.
Length, on fourth stump. Root defends it to point.
FOUR! Top innovation! It is full, wide outside off. Joe Root shuffles across a long way and reverse scoops it over the first slip. The ball runs down to the third man fence.
Full and on off. Root drives it to sweeper cover and collects a brace.
Length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and chops it to backward point.
This is on a good length and on off, Harry Brook dabs it towards point.
A bit fuller and on off, Harry Brook blocks it out to the off side.
Full again and on middle, shaping in, Harry Brook looks to play at it, but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
On a length and on leg, Harry Brook misses his flick and the ball goes off his pads towards square leg. The batters run a leg bye.
Pitched up, on middle, Joe Root moves across and clips it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook looks defend but gets a bottom edge onto his pads as the ball rolls behind the stumps.
FOUR! Nice shot! Neil Wagner serves this full and around off, Joe Root gets to the pitch of it and drives it with sweet timng past mid on for a boundary. He moves to 99 now!
On a length and on off, Joe Root steers it towards gully.
Full and on middle, Joe Root turns it towards short mid-wicket.
This is on a hard length and on off, Joe Root moves across but flicks it straight to short mid-wicket.
Overpitched and on middle, Joe Root clips it but finds short mid-wicket again.

HUNDRED FOR ROOT! A fine knock from him after a run of low scores. He punches the air in celebration. Joe Root comes down the track, makes this a full toss, on middle, and whips it towards wide of deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Matt Henry starts with a good-length delivery, on off, Harry Brook looks to block, but gets an outside edge towards third slip on the bounce.
This is full and on middle, Harry Brook tries to drive it away, but gets an inside edge through mid-wicket for a couple of runs. First runs of the Day!
Full again and around off, Harry Brook blocks it with one hand as he lose his grip when the ball hits his bat.
Matt Henry bangs in a bouncer, on off, Harry Brook lets it go to the keeper.

Back of a length and on off, Harry Brook looks to punch it away, but gets an insdie edge onto his pads. He is not finding the middle of the bat here and the Kiwis need to take advantage of this situation.
On a length and on off, Harry Brook dabs it towards slip cordon where the fielder dives to his left to make a good stop.
Tim Southee begins with a hard-length delivery, on off, Joe Root leans on and knocks it towards short covers.
Fuller one and on middle, Joe Root uses his feet, but mistimes his drive towards mid on.
Full again and on off, Joe Root keeps it out to the left of short covers.

SIX! Cheeky but effective! Tim Southee serves this fuller once more around off, Joe Root moves across and reverse scoops it over the third man fence for a biggie. Tim Southee was not expecting something like this from Root that too so early in the Day. Also, 300-run partnership comes up between these two battters.
On a length and on off, Joe Root defends it towards short covers.
Short of a length and on off, Joe Root cuts it close from his body, but straight to gully.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Matt Henry strikes again! Harry Brook misses out on his double hundred, but he has played an exceptional innings here. Matt Henry pitches this up, on middle, Harry Brook goes for the drive on the up, but does so uppishly towards the bowler where Matt Henry attempts to catch it, but it spills out to his left. However, he shows good reflexes to go down and pouches it with his left hand. A fine catch to end a fine innings. Harry Brook looked unsettled and he will be disappointed that he missed out on a moment of history here.
Howout: c & b Matt Henry

Commentary: On a length and on middle, Ben Stokes turns it to the leg side.
Short of a length and outside off, angling away with extra bounce, Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
FOUR! Ben Stokes gets off the mark with a boundary! Matt Henry bowls this back of a length but down the leg, Ben Stokes just tickles it towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
FOUR! Two in a row! Matt Henry serves this full and around off, Ben Stokes advances down the track and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Fuller again and on off, Ben Stokes pushes it towards short covers.
This is on a good length and on off, Joe Root looks to defend it, but gets a bottom edge onto his pads and then the ball bounces and hits his bat again.

In the air...safe! Tim Southee bangs this short and on middle, Joe Root uses his feet but gets hurried and miscues his pull in the air. However, the wind drifts it away form the fielder at deep mid-wicket and it falls safely. Two runs taken!
Fullish and around leg, Joe Root clips it wide of deep square leg for a brace.
Full again and on middle, Joe Root tucks it through square leg for a run.
On a length and around off, angling in, Ben Stokes offers no shot at it.
Length again and on middle this time, Ben Stokes blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and on off, Joe Root waits for it and late cuts it, but the fielder at slip corden dives to his right to make a one-handed stop.
Goes fuller this time, on middle, Joe Root flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Matt Henry bangs in a high bouncer, on middle and off, Ben Stokes sways away from it.
Full and on off, Ben Stokes makes some room and forces it straight to mid off.
FOUR! Up and over! Matt Henry bowls this short of a length and outside off, Ben Stokes backs away again and slaps it over point for a boundary.
This is pitched up and around off, Ben Stokes moves across and tries to play the scoop, but misses as the ball goes under his bat towards the keeper. He has made his intentions clear here.
Full and on off, Joe Root drives it back towards the bowler.
Tim Southee lands this short and on middle, Joe Root controls his pull shot towards deep square leg for a single.

Uppish but safe! Tim Southee bowls this short and on off, Ben Stokes makes room, but miscues his slog in the air behind the bowler. The fielder from mid on chases it, but fails to reach it. They cross.
On a length and on middle, Joe Root tucks it through mid-wicket for a run.
Length again and on off, Ben Stokes defends it towards short covers.
BEAUTY! Tim Southee goes a bit fuller and on off, shaping away slightly, Ben Stokes gets squared up as he tries to block and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short of a length and on off, Joe Root is on his toes to keep it down towards gully beacause of the extra bounce.
This is on a good length and on middle, Joe Root nudges it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on middle, Ben Stokes blocks it down the pitch.
Overpitched and on off, Ben Stokes drills it wide of deep point and comes back for the second easily.
FOUR! Brilliant shot! Matt Henry bowls this just short and around off, Ben Stokes backs away a bit and cuts it well towards the deep backward point fence for a boundary.
Another full delivery, on off, Ben Stokes drives it towards short covers.
Neil Wagner starts with a good-length delivery, on off, Joe Root pushes it through cover-point for a single.
Neil Wagner follows the batter and lands this on a hard length, on leg, angling in, Ben Stokes gets cramped and misses his flick as the ball goes off his pads to the off side.
On a length and around leg, Ben Stokes nudges it through square leg for one.
Back of a length and on off, Joe Root guides it towards gully.
Goes fuller and on middle, Joe Root skips down the track and heaves it towards deep mid-wicket for one.
Back of a length again and on off, Ben Stokes backs away and punches it towards sweeper covers for one more.
Michael Bracewell begins with a low full toss, on off, Ben Stokes goes for the reverse-sweep, but misses to get hit on his toes. There is a stiffled appeal for LBW, but turned down.
Tossed up, full and on off, Ben Stokes drives it towards short covers.
FOUR! Ben Stokes connects this time! This is floated, full and on off, Ben Stokes nails his reverse-sweep past backward point for a boundary.
Slower through the air, on middle, turning away, Ben Stokes looks to push it away, but gets an outiside on the bounce and past slips for a couple of runs.
Flighted, full and on off, Ben Stokes knocks it towards covers.
Gives this one some air, on off, turning away with some bounce, Ben Stokes looks for the reverse-sweep again, but misses due to the bounce.
Full and on middle, Joe Root flicks it through square leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Ben Stokes tries to go big, but holes out instead. Neil Wagner bowls this short of a length and outside off, Ben Stokes backs away and tries to clear the in-field on the off side, but mistimes his shot badly in the air and Scott Kuggeleijn (Sub) at mid off moves to his right to take a good catch. Stokes was looking to score runs quickly, but he will have to go back now. England lose half their side now!
Howout: c sub Scott Kuggeleijn b Neil Wagner

Commentary: Full and on middle, Ben Foakes drives it towards mid on.
Full again and on middle, Ben Foakes knocks it towards mid on again.
Overpitched and on off, Ben Foakes drives it well, but straight to mid off.
This is on a good length and outside off, Ben Foakes leaves it alone. End of a successful over for New Zealand!
A bit flatter, around leg. Root goes back and nudges it past short leg for a single.

OUT! STUMPED! Another one bites the dust. Ben Foakes gifts his wicket to the Kiwis. It is tossed up, around off. Ben Foakes steps out of the crease and tries to flick it away but misses. The ball grips and tunrs down leg as well. Ben Foakes' gets his front foot stuck on the deck and that makes him fall over. Tom Blundell gathers the ball and takes the bails off in a flash. Ben Foakes walks back without troubling the score.
Howout: st Tom Blundell b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Floated and full, outside off. It grips and turns away. Stuart Broad makes a leave.

Just past short leg! It is angled in around middle. Stuart Broad bends his knee and tries to sweep it away. The ball goes past short leg off the bottom end. Tom Latham dives to his left but the ball goes past him. Two taken.
On off, blocked.
Flatter and on off. Broad stays back and dabs it past the slip fielder. A successful over from Michael Bracewell comes to an end.

An appeal for lbw but turned down! Neil Wagner comes from around the wicket. It is angled in, on a length and around off. Joe Root shuffles and goes for the scoop. He misses to get any bat on it. Neil Wagner appeals but the umpire shows no interest. Tim Southee takes the review with 1 second on the time. Although, the Ball Tracking confirms that the impact is outside the line. New Zealand lose all their reviews here.
Full and on off. Joe Root pushes it to cover and crosses.
FOUR! Up and over! Broad frees his arms here. It is a bit short, on fourth stump. Stuart Broad rides the bounce and smacks it over mid off for a boundary.
This is much fuller, on fourth stump. Broad makes some room and dabs it towards covers.
Neil Wagner follows the batter down leg with a length ball. Stuart Broad only manages to get an inside edge on his pads.
Three dots in a row to end the over! It is a good-lenght ball, angled into the body. Stuart Broad swivels and goes for the pull shot, but it dies off the inside edge.
SIX! SMACKED! Joe Root is shifting gears here. It is tossed up, outside off. Joe Root dances down the track and slogs it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
This is full and on leg. Joe Root gets low and drags his sweep down to fine leg. They take two runs.
Short, turning in from outside off. Root pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Looped up, around off. Broad gets an inside edge on it. It goes through his legs and even nutmegs Tom Latham on the way at short leg. The batters take a couple.
On off, defended out.
Full, on middle and leg. Broad clips it towards short mid-wicket.
A length ball, angled in on middle. Joe Root gets down and sweeps it towards fine leg. It comes off his gloves and they take a single.
A well-directed short ball, on off. Stuart Broad tries to hook it away but fails to connect.
FOUR! EDGY! Neil Wagner goes short again, outside off. Stuart Broad shuts his eyes, and heaves hard across the line. The ball takes the outside edge and flies down to third man for four.
A slower full toss, on the body. Broad goes back and works it towards mid off. They take a single.
Length and on the pads. Joe Root whips it behind square on the leg side for one.
It is full, on leg. Stuart Broad hangs back and flicks it to deep mid-wicket. He retains the strike with a single.
Tossed up, full and on off. Broad eases it to mid off.

OUT! LBW! Michael Bracewell gets his second wicket of the morning, as the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Stuart Broad though takes the review straightaway. It is a loopy ball, that drifts in, around middle and turns away a touch. Stuart Broad gets down on one knee and tries to sweep it away. He fails to get any bat on it and takes a blow on his pads. The umpire agrees with Michael Bracewell. The review taken does not help Stuart Broad at all, as the Ball Tracking shows three reds. The on-field decision stands.
Howout: lbw b Michael Bracewell

Commentary: Floated, wide of off. It turns in a long way. Ollie Robinson stays back and nudges it to the leg side.
Goes full and on off. Ollie Robinson dabs it into the deck.
Loopy ball, outside off. It grips and turns in a long way. Ollie Robinson prods and tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the inside edge.
Fuller, on leg. Ollie Robinson clips it to mid-wicket and gets off the mark with a single here.
Some shape straightaway. A length ball, outside off. It shapes away. Ollie Robinson is happy with a sighter here.
JAFFA! Ollie Robinson gets his blade out of the way. It is a length ball, in the channel. The ball flies off the deck. Ollie Robinson gets beaten on the outside edge.

Length and on off. Ollie Robinson pushes it to cover for a single. Meanwhile, Ben Stokes is seen having a chat with his coach here. There is a bright smile across Stokes' face. He is certainly itching to get out here with the ball in hand. The conditions are heavenly for the seamers here with the new ball.
Good length, wide of off. It nips in a long way with some extra bounce. Joe Root gets on his front foot and tries to drive it through the line but gets beaten.

SIX! BANG! Looks like a declaration is around the corner. It is a length ball, on off. Joe Root gets to the pitch of the ball, removes any threat for any swing and smokes it over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum.
FOUR! Exceptional shot. It is full and on off. Joe Root shuffles across and scoops it over the wicket-keeper's head for four runs. 400 is up for England.
Good length, in the channel. Ollie Robinson dabs it down to gully.
A length ball, on off. Ollie Robinson taps it to off and takes off to the other end.
Good length, around off. Root gets behind and blocks it back to the bowler.
FOUR! This is brutal. Henry goes full, on sixth stump. Joe Root shuffles way across and scoops it down to fine leg. One bounce and over the ropes.
Short and on the body. Joe Root stays back and pulls it to deep square leg, only for a single. He moves to 147.
Length and on the pads, Ollie Robinson clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Tim Southee fires it full, around leg. Ollie Robinson stays back and tries to flick it away but misses. Tim Southee makes a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. It is going down leg.
FOUR! EDGY! It is a length ball, on off. Ollie Robinson tries to flick it through the leg side. The ball takes the leading edge and flies to third man for four runs.
A bit fuller, on middle. Ollie Robinson goes back and lofts it over mid on. They take two runs.
A bit short, outside off. Ollie Robinson stays back and tries to cut it away but misses.
Another dot now, as Ollie Robinson hangs back to this length ball and dabs it to covers.
This is a length ball, that lands around off and shapes away sharply. Ollie Robinson makes a good leave here.
A length ball, outside off, it shapes further away. Joe Root tries to block it but does so inside the line.
Full length, on off. Joe Root gets an inside edge on his pads.
Matt Henry sees the batter come down the track and serves a short ball, on off. Joe Root makes a late adjustment and pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
WIDE! A sharp bumper, on off. Ollie Robinson ducks under it. The umpire signals a wide.
Short one, around off. Ollie Robinson lets it be.
It is full, tailing into the pads. Ollie Robinson pushes it gently towards mid off.
A length ball, on middle. Ollie Robinson tucks it to the leg side. Matt Henry sprints to that side and stops the ball with a dive to that side. One taken.
Tim Southee dishes a length ball, on middle. Ollie Robinson goes back and drills it down to long on for a couple.

Much fuller, on off. Ollie Robinson gets under it and plays a lofted drive straight down the ground. He does not get it off the middle of the blade and Neil Wagner is able to keep it down to two runs.
In the air...Safe! It is a short one, on off. Ollie Robinson goes for the pull but mistimes it towards deep mid-wicket. Two fielders converge but it falls in no man's land. Two taken.
Length and on off, defended out.
Fuller and on leg. Ollie Robinson shuffles and tucks it to short mid-wicket. Wait is the call here.

Back of a length, on off. Ollie Robinson hooks it to deep square leg. The batters take one more. Ollie Robinson takes the strike once again, while Root is made to wait here to get yet another milestone in this Test match.
Goes full and on leg. Ollie Robinson tucks it towards mid on.
A length ball, on fourth stump. Ollie Robinson blocks it out solidly.

DROPPED! Completely unacceptable from Tom Blundell. It is a length ball, around off, nips away a touch. Ollie Robinson only manages to get a thick outside edge on it. Tom Blundell moves to his right but the ball spills out of his gloves.

OUT! CAUGHT! Matt Henry gets his fourth wicket. It is a length ball, on off. Ollie Robinson ends up chipping it towards mid off. Tom Latham there takes a dolly. A huge sigh of relief for Tom Blundell. Jack Leach is the new man in.
Howout: c Tim Southee b Matt Henry

Commentary: On a length, outside off, left alone.
Much fuller, outside off. It nips in a touch. Jack Leach tries to chase it but misses.
A full-length ball, angled into the pads. Joe Root charges down and looks to go downtown but misses.
Short and on off. Root pulls it to deep mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on off. Joe Root pulls it along the ground to deep mid-wicket for one.
Slower one, full and outside off. Leach drives it into covers.
It is pitched up, outside off. Jack Leach leans in and pushes it firmly through the gap at covers for two runs here. He gets off the mark.

FOUR! Off the edge! It is fired in full and on off. Jack Leach tries to flick it away but is a bit early into his shot. The ball catches the outside edge and flies over the slip cordon for a boundary.

FOUR! 150 up for Joe Root. He gets there in style and that should be it. Joe Root is seen jogging out of the field here. Full and on the pads. Joe Root flicks it to deep square leg for four runs. England declare at 435/8.
James Anderson starts with a hard-length delivery, on middle, Tom Latham stays back and blocks it down the pitch.
Tom Latham and New Zealand are underway! This is full and on middle, Tom Latham turns it in front of short mid-wicket for a single.
Full again and on middle, Devon Conway knocks it to the leg side.
Good bowling! James Anderson bowls this back of a length and on middle, shaping in sharply, Devon Conway offers no shot at it, and gets hit on his stomach area.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! What a start from England! James Anderson draws first blood! He serves this touch fuller and on off,angling away this time, Devon Conway looks to defend, but the angle takes a thin outside edge towards the keeper where Ben Foakes pouches it safely. There is a stiffled appeal for caught behind, but turned down. Ben Stokes takes the review though after some discussion. UltraEdge confirms that Conway has hit it and England players are delighted. Devon Conway has to make that long walk back to the hut now without troubling the scorers.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b James Anderson

Commentary: On a length and on off, Kane Williamson steers it towards gully.
Stuart Broad begins with a full delivery but way down the leg side, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Full again and down the leg again, Tom Latham misses his flick this time.
Pitched up, on off, angling in, Tom Latham looks to play at it, but gets an inside edge onto his pads as the ball rolls to the off side.
Overpitched and on middle, angling in, Tom Latham tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Stuart Broad continues with the fuller length, on middle, Tom Latham keeps it out to the leg side.
Stuart Broad strays away from his line again and serves this full but down the leg side one more time, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
This is full and on middle, Kane Williamson looks to defend it, but gets a leading edge through point for a single and gets off the mark.
Full again and on middle, Tom Latham knocks it back towards the bowler.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham guides it towards gully.
This is on a hard length in the channel outsdide off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Overpitched and outside off, Tom Latham drives it through point for a couple of runs.
Pitched up, on off, Tom Latham pushes it towards short covers.
This is full and on off, Kane Williamson tries to defend it but gets an outside edge past gully, Harry Brook chases it and slides in and just manages to keep it inside. Three runs taken!
Stuart Broad is struggling with his line to the left-hander here. He bowls this full again but down the leg side, Tom Latham misses his flick.
Another full delivery, on off, Tom Latham blocks it to the off side.
Pulls his length back a bit, outside off, nips away, Tom Latham is not interested to play that.
Goes back to his fuller length, on middle, Tom Latham turns it towards short leg.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham pushes it towards short covers, Kane Williamson wants the run, but he is sent back.
BEAUTY! James Anderson lands this short of a length and on off, takes off with extra bounce, Kane Williamson gets hurried and gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to fend it.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson strikes again! Kane Williamson's woes continue as he walks back for yet another low score. James Anderson this time serves this slightly fuller than the previous delivery around off, shaping away, Kane Williamson looks to push it away without any footwork and gets a thin outside edge towards the keeper where Ben Foakes makes no mistake. New Zealand two down now!
Howout: c Ben Foakes b James Anderson

Commentary: Touch fuller and around off, Will Young lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
This is on a good length and on the sixth stump line, shaping in, Will Young leaves it alone.
Pitched up, on middle, Will Young tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Ona length, on off, angling in, Will Young strides forward and looks to defend, but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a shout for LBW, but turned down. Ben Stokes decides against the review.
Ollie Robinson starts with a full delivery and on middle, Tom Latham blocks it down the pitch.
Full again and on leg, Tom Latham works it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and on middle, Tom Latham looks to defend, but gets an outside edge on the bounce towards gully.
BEATEN! Ollie Robinson bowls this on a hard length and just around off, angling away, Tom Latham looks to play at it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and outside off, angling away, Tom Latham shoulders arms to it.
A maided over! Ollie Robinson serves this touch fuller, outside off, Tom Latham offers no shot at it.
Full and on middle, Will Young flicks it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham steers it towards gully.
EDGED AND FOUR! This is short of a length and outside off, Tom Latham slashes hard at it, and it goes well over the slips towards the third man fence for a boudnary.
Pitched up, on middle, Tom Latham works it towards short mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on middle, Tom Latham stays back and keeps it out to the leg side.
Overpitched and on off, Tom Latham drives it towards short covers. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Full and on off, Will Young pushes it towards covers for a single.
Full again and around off, Tom Latham drills it through cover-point for a brace.
FOUR! Fine shot! Stuart Broad serves a hafl-volley, outside off, Tom Latham shows the full face of the bat to drive it through covers for a beautiful boundary.
Pitched up, on leg, Tom Latham clips it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham knocks it towards short covers.
Touch fuller and outside off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on middle, angling in, Will Young defends it towards short leg.
Goes fuller and on off, Will Young leans on and fends it to the right of gully.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! James Anderson gets rid of Will Young with a peach of a delivery. He lands this on a good length with the angle and in the channel outside off, nips away just a bit, Will Young tries to play at it, but the movement away takes a slight nick towards the keeper where Ben Foakes takes his third catch of this innings. Young could not have done much there as this was just perfect from James Anderson.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b James Anderson

Commentary: On a length and on off, angling away, Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Length again and outside off again, Henry Nicholls offers no shot at it.
FOUR! Henry Nicholls gets off the mark with a boundary! James Anderson bowls this back of a length and outside off, Henry Nicholls stays there and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Fuller one and on middle, Tom Latham keeps it out towards short leg.
Full again and on off, Tom Latham drives it towards short covers.
This is on a hard length and outside off, shaping furhter away, Tom Latham is not interested to play that.
Back of a length and around off, shaping away again, Tom Latham is in two mind whether to play it or not, and withdraws his bat at the last moment.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham dabs it towards gully.
Touch fuller and outside off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on leg, Henry Nicholls nudges it towards short fine leg.
FOUR! Good shot! James Anderson serves this full and on middle, Henry Nicholls stays there and drives it towards the vacant long on fence for a boundary.
Pulls his length back a bit, on leg, Henry Nicholls tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Length again, on middle, Henry Nicholls misses his flick and gets hit high on his body.
FOUR! Nice timing! This on a hard length and around leg, Henry Nicholls flicks it with great timing towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
A bit fuller and on off, Henry Nicholls pushes it towards covers.
EDGED AND FOUR! This is on a good length and on off, angling in, Tom Latham looks to fend it, but gets an outside edge on the bounce and between gully and third slip for a boundary.
Length again and outside off, Tom Latham shoulders arms to it.
Touch fuller, outside off, shaping away, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Full again and on middle, angling in, Tom Latham misses his flick and gets hit on the thigh pads.
Pitched up, on off, Tom Latham works it with the outer half through point for a single.
Stuart Broad continues with the fuller length, on leg this time, Henry Nicholls tucks it through mid-wicket for three runs.
Full and on off, Henry Nicholls pushes it to the right of short covers for a single.
Full again and on leg, Tom Latham turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller once more, on middle, Tom Latham blocks it back to the bowler.
Overpitched and around off, Tom Latham drills it through covers as Ben Duckett chases it. The batters take on the arm and completes three runs.
On a length and on leg, Henry Nicholls nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
This is on a good length and on off, straightens after hitting the deck, Tom Latham looks to play at it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Ollie Robinson begins with a pitched-up delivery, on middle, Henry Nicholls works it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and around leg, Henry Nicholls keeps it out down the pitch.
Length again and on the sixth stump line, angling away, Henry Nicholls leaves it alone.
Goes a bit fuller and on off, angling away again, Henry Nicholls lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller once more, on middle, angling in, Henry Nicholls knocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length and around off, Henry Nicholls moves across and has a nibble at it, but gets beaten on the outside edge due to the extra bounce.
Stuart Broad nails the yorker, on off, angling in, Tom Latham digs it out back towards the bowler.
Another yorker, on middle, Tom Latham jams it out towards short mid-wicket.
Overpiched and on off, Tom Latham drives it towards covers for a single.
On a length and on middle, angling in, Henry Nicholls looks to block it, but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a slight appeal for LBW, but turned down.
Goes back to his fuller length, on middle, angling in, Henry Nicholls fends it to the left of the bowler.
This is on a hard length and on middle, Henry Nicholls keeps it out to the leg side.
Ollie Robinson comes from 'round the wicket. It is a length ball, angled in around off. Tom Latham defends it out solidly.
It is much fuller, on off. Tom Latham gets on his front foot and blocks it back to the bowler off the toe end.
Three dots in a row! It is full, angled into the pads. Tom Latham blocks it to the leg side off the inner half.
Make that four! Ollie Robinson now changes the angle as he comes from over the wicket. It is on a good-length, angling across the left-hander. Left alone.
Good leave! It is a length ball, that lands around middle and nips away a touch. Tom Latham trusts the bounce here and shoulders his arms at it.
Much fuller, outside off, shaping away off the deck. Tom Latham has no shot to offer. Third consecutive maiden for Ollie Robinson.
Shortish, around off. Henry Nicholls charges down the wicket and flicks it towards mid-wicket. One taken.
Much fuller, angled in around off. Tom Latham closes the face and tucks it to the leg side.
On a length, on fifth stump. Tom Latham get forward and dabs it out to safety.
Outside off, left alone.
Broad goes full, outside off. Tom Latham lets it be.
Broad dishes a full ball, outside off. Tom Latham gets on his front foot and punches it through the gap at covers. The batters take three runs before the fielder cuts it off.

Close! It is a length ball, that lands outside off and shapes in off the deck. Although, the bounce takes it over the stumps. Tom Latham makes a good leave here. Ollie Robinson cannot believe how has this not hit the stumps.
BEATEN! Ollie Robinson now serves it on a length, outside off. It nips away off the deck. Tom Latham tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on off, blocked out.
Ollie Robinson dishes a length ball, on off. Tom Latham flicks it to the right of short leg. Ollie Pope is quick to react. He dives to his right and makes a sharp stop.
On off, blocked out solidly.
A length ball, in the channel. Tom Latham gets on his front foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Floats it up, full and outside off. Henry Nicholls presses forward and blocks.

Shouts of 'catch it'! It is looped up, around off, with some extra bounce off the deck. Henry Nicholls prods and tries to sweep it away. He misses, although it lobs off his arms and lands short of the man at leg slip.
Much better connection! Tossed up, full and outside off. Henry Nicholls gets low and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for one.
On the pads, tucked past Ollie Pope on the leg side.
SIX! BANG! Jack Leach goes full and on off. Tom Latham dances down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and smokes it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
A bit short, on middle and leg. Tom Latham flicks it to square leg for a single.
Ollie Robinson pitches it up, full and on off. Tom Latham dabs it out to the off side.
It is full, angled into the pads. Tom Latham hangs back and flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Robinson dishes a length ball, around off. It nips in off the deck. Henry Nicholls tries to flick it away but gets pinged on his pads. A stifled appeal but the umpire shows no interest.
Outside off, left alone.
It is full, on off. Henry Nicholls presses forward  and defends it out solidly.
Robinson serves it full, on fifth stump. Henry Nicholls shuffles across to defend it out. Just a single run off it.
Tossed up, around off, turning in. Tom Latham clips it to the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Matter of inches here. Tom Latham is extremely gutted as he trudges back to the dressing room. Some 'boos' can be heard from the crowd as well. The fans are not holding themselves back here from expressing their feelings. It is tossed up, around off. Tom Latham goes for the reverse sweep but misses. The ball lobs off his gloves and Joe Root takes a dolly at first slip. An appeal is made and up goes the dreaded finger. Tom Latham though takes the review instantly. He thinks that iths comes off his arm guard. The third umpire goes through the replays several times. In the front-on vision it looks like it comes arm guard first, although, the side-on angle shows that the ball first comes in contact with the top of the glove. The third umpire asks the on-field umpire to stick with the original decision.
Howout: c Joe Root b Jack Leach

Commentary: FOUR! Daryl Mitchell gets off the mark in style! This is floated, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and drives it past the bowler for a boundary.
Slowr through the air, on off, turning away, Daryl Mitchell fends it to the off side.
Quicker, short and on middle, Daryl Mitchell moves back and blocks it out.
Flighted, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell leans on and nudges it to the leg side.
On a length and on middle, Henry Nicholls nudges it towards square leg for a single.
It is a length ball, on off. Daryl Mitchell shuffles and blocks it out.
Much fuller, outside off. Daryl Mitchell gets forward and blocks it to mid off.

Ollie Robinson dishes a length ball, outside off. It nips in off the deck. Daryl Mitchell presses forward and tries to defend it out. He gets a thick inside edge onto his pads. The ball pops up but does not carry towards the keeper.
Length, outside off, left alone.
On a good length, on fifth stump, jabs back in late. Daryl Mitchell shuffles and makes a good leave.
It is full and outside off. Henry Nicholls gets low and sweeps it to the right of short third man. The batters take two runs.
FOUR! Nicely played! Jack Leach goes full once again, outside off. Henry Nicholls gets down on one knee and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Fuller, on the pads. Henry Nicholls nudges it to the leg side.
Flatter and on off. Henry Nicholls goes back and knocks it towards mid on.
FOUR! Top shot! Second boundary of the over. Jack Leach goes full, on middle. Henry Nicholls prods and the broom comes out once again. Nicholls sweeps it behind square for another boundary.
On off, Henry Nicholls blocks it out solidly.
Robinson starts this over with a full one, outside off. Daryl Mitchell tries to punch it through the line but gets it to square leg off the inside edge. The batters take a couple.
Length, on sixth stump. Daryl Mitchell shuffles and defends it to cover.
Too full and straight, around off. Daryl Mitchell helps it back to the bowler.
On a length, in the channel. Daryl Mitchell presses forward and defends it to covers.
Swing and a miss! Ollie Robinson serves a length ball, wide of off. Daryl Mitchell comes across a long way to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Ollie Robinson serves a length ball, outside off. It jabs back in with some extra bounce. Daryl Mitchell shoulders his arms at it and takes a blow near the stomach area.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Henry Nicholls nudges it towards mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! New Zealand now have half of their side sent back to the hut. A horrible dismissal here. Jack Leach gets his second wicket in no time. It is tossed up, around middle. Henry Nicholls switches his stance and goes for the reverse sweep. It brushes his gloves and pops up. The ball goes to the left of short leg. Ollie Pope dives that side and takes a stunning one-handed catch.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Jack Leach

Commentary: On middle and leg, tucked away to the leg side.
Flights it up, on off. It grips and turns away off the deck, Tom Blundell tries to go after it but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
On off, blocked out.
Flatter and on middle. Tom Blundell goes back and nudges it to the leg side for one. He gets off the mark here.
Full and outside off, Tom Blundell prods forward and leaves it alone.
This is on a good length and on off, angling in sharply, Tom Blundell lets it got to the keeper. Good leave!
Goes fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell drills it towards short mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back a bit, on middle, Tom Blundell defends it to the leg side.
Length again and around off, Tom Blundell steers it through point for a couple of runs.
Ollie Robinson lands this on a hard length and outside off, shaping away, Tom Blundell offers no shot at it.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell leans on and blocks it out.
Floated and on middle, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet to knock it towards short mid-wicket where the fielder dives to his left to stop the single.
Flighted, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it on the front foot.
On middle, blocked out.
A bit short and on off, Daryl Mitchell moves back and punches it towards covers.
A maiden over! This is flatter and outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
This is on a hard length and on middle, angling in, Tom Blundell looks to work it away, but misses and gets hit high on his body.
FOUR! Nice shot! James Anderson serves this full and on off, Tom Blundell stays there and drives it firmly towards the vacant long off fence for a boundary.
On a length and on middle, Tom Blundell blocks it down the pitch.
Length again and on middle, angling in, Tom Blundell tries to fend it away, but gets a bottom edge onto his pads as the ball goes nowhere.
Goes a bit fuller and on off, shaping in, Tom Blundell makes another good leave.
Back of a length and on off, Tom Blundell steers it towards point.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell leans on and blocks it to the right of the bowler.
Floated, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it down the pitch.
Gives this one some air, on middle, turning away, Daryl Mitchell moves back and keeps it down to the off side.
