Flighted, full and on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it uppishly but wide of short mid-wicket for a brace.
Slower through the air, on off, Daryl Mitchell fends it to the right of silly point.
Ripper! This is floated, on off, grips and turns away sharply, Daryl Mitchell is beateon on the outside edge as he tries to defend.
Full and on off, Tom Blundell pushes it towards covers for a single.
On a length and on off, nips back in, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Back of a length and on leg, Daryl Mitchell nudges it towards square leg for a single.
This is on a good length and on off, Tom Blundell knocks it towards covers.
Touch fuller and on off, Tom Blundell offers no shot at it.
Full again and on middle, Tom Blundell drives it towards short mid on where a fumble allows a run.
Short and on middle, Tom Blundell moves back and punches it towards short covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Tom Blundell blocks it to the leg side.
Slightly shorter and on off, Tom Blundell forces it wide of mid off for a single.
Short again and on off, Daryl Mitchell pushes it, but it hits the fielder at silly point and goes nowhere.
Gives this one some air, on off, Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Flatter, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell works it with the inner half towards square leg.
On a length and on off, Tom Blundell knocks it towards short covers.
Fuller one and on off, Tom Blundell drives it firmly, but the fielder at short covers dives to his right to stop it.
Pulls his length back a bit, on middle, Tom Blundell pushes it towards short covers.
Length again and on middle, Tom Blundell tucks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Overpitched and on off, Daryl Mitchell is solid in his defense again.
Pitched up, on middle, Daryl Mitchell glances it towards the vacant deep mid-wicket region where the ball stops due to the slow outfield. Three runs taken!
Tossed up, full and on off, Daryl Mitchell blocks it out.
Floated, full and on off, Daryl Mitchell works it with the inner half towards square leg for a single.
Short and on middle, Tom Blundell tucks it through mid-wicket for one.
Flighted, full and on middle, Daryl Mitchell knocks it back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked out.

OUT! TAKEN! A splendid catch to get rid of Daryl Mitchell! New Zealand lose a wicket on the last ball of the second session. Jack Leach gives this one some air, on off, Daryl Mitchell prods forward to defend, but is a bit early into his shot, and rather than hitting the ball, the ball hit his bat and loops up in the air, Ollie Pope at silly point shows great reflexes and grabs it with his outstreched right hand. England players celebrate, but Daryl Mitchell will be kicking himself. New Zealand six down now! THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 2!
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Jack Leach

Commentary: This is on a good length and on middle, Tom Blundell nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length and on off, angling in, Tom Blundell keeps it out towards short covers.
On a length and on off, Tom Blundell pushes it wide of short covers for a quick single.
Goes full and on middle, angling in, Michael Bracewell tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Short of a length and on leg, Michael Bracewell clips it towards deep square leg for a run and gets off the mark.
A bit fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell defends it out with the inner half of his bat.
Quicker, short and on leg, Michael Bracewell moves back and flicks it towards square leg.
Short again and on leg, Michael Bracewell turns it towards backward short leg.
FOUR! Good shot! This is tossed up, full and on leg, Michael Bracewell goes down and nails his sweep towards the deep backward square leg fence for a boundary.
Shortish and around leg, Michael Bracewell heaves it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
Floated, full and on middle, Tom Blundell defends it on the front foot.
Tossed up, full and on off, Tom Blundell blocks it towards silly point.
This is on a good length and on off, Michael Bracewell turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Back of a length and outside off, Michael Bracewell leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Stuart Broad finally gets a wicket! He lands this on a hard length and around off, angling in, Michael Bracewell is anticipating a fuller length and is early into his defensive shot, and the ball lobs up off the bat towards the bowler where Stuart Broad takes a dolly. He cannot believe his luck while Bracewell stands there in disbelief as well. New Zealand in huge trouble as they are seven down now!
Howout: c & b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Full and on off, Tim Southee knocks it to the left of short covers for a quick single.
This is on a hard length and on off, angling in, Tom Blundell makes an easy leave.
Pitched up, on off, Tom Blundell drives it wide of point where the fielder dives to his right to stop it. They cross.
Flatter, short and on middle, Tom Blundell makes room and punches it towards point.
Short again and on off, Tom Blundell pushes it towards short covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Tom Blundell leans on and blocks it out.
Floated, full and on off, Tom Blundell drives it towards long off for a single.
Darts this one full and on middle, Tim Southee nudges it towards mid-wicket for a run.
FOUR! Powered away! This is short and around off, Tom Blundell makes some room and smashes it over mid on for a boundary.
SIX! BANG! Tim Southee goes big now! This is on a good length and on middle, Tim Southee clears his front leg and slogs it over the wide long on fence for a biggie.
Touch fuller and on off, Tim Southee heaves it towards mid-wicket where the fielder dives to his right to stop it.
On a length and on off, Tim Southee taps it in front of point for a single.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Tom Blundell lets it go to the keeper.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off, Tom Blundell pushes it towards short covers. There is a bit of hesitation between the batters, but no harm done in the end.
Length again and on middle, Tom Blundell pats it back towards the bowler.
Shortish, outside off. Tim Southee stays back and punches it to cover.
Full and on off. Tim Southee gets forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Tosses it up, full, on off. Tim Southee presses forward and gets it to point off the outer half.
On off, defended out solidly.
Leach serves it full, sliding down leg. Tim Southee tickles it down to fine leg for a brace.
Full and on off. Southee dabs it to silly point, on a bounce though. Just a couple of the over.
On a length, outside off, nips back in off the deck. Tom Blundell gets forward to block it out firmly.
Broad goes a bit fuller this time, swinging in on off. Tom Blundell fends it out to the off side.
Full length, drifting down leg. Tom Blundell clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.

FOUR! EDGY! Some lucky finally on New Zealand's side. It is a short ball, outside off. Tim Southee stands tall and heaves across the line. The ball catches the top-edge, flies over the keeper's head for four runs. It certainly does not matter how the runs come now.
SIX! Tim Southee is making his intent clear. It is short, on middle. Tim Southee makes some room and launches it over the cow corner fence for a biggie.
A bit slower, full and on off. Tim Southee shuffles and tucks it to the leg side. 11 runs off the over. The skipper is turning on the heat with the bat in hand here.
Full and on middle. Tom Blundell blocks it on his front foot.
Much fuller, around off. Tom Blundell defends it into the deck.
Flatter and on middle. Tom Blundell goes back and tries to pull it away. It rolls out to the leg side off the inside edge.
On off, defended out.
Flatter, outside off. Tom Blundell plays it late to Joe Root at first slip.
FOUR! Sweet timing! It is short, in the channel. Tom Blundell gets on his back and cuts it hard and flat through point. The ball races away to the fence.
A length ball, outside off, it jags back in a touch. Tim Southee tries to flick it to the leg side but is a bit early into his shot. The ball goes to covers off his fingers. One taken.
Broad fires it full, down leg. Tom Blundell stays inside the crease and wrists it gently to mid-wicket for one more.
It is very full, on fourth stump. Tim Southee goes back and jams it back to the bowler. Broad is quick to get low and stop the ball.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping further away. Tim Southee looks to cut it away but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length, in the channel. Tim Southee gets it to cover off the outer half. They take a single.
Broad goes full, on fifth stump. Tom Blundell steps across and blocks it under his eyes. New Zealand trail by 297 runs.

Ollie Robinson starts with a bouncer, on off. This one flies off the deck. Tim Southee gets on his toes and blocks it off the top half of the blade. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.

Robinson now delivers it on a length, on fourth stump. Tim Southee stays back and punches it through the gap at covers. The batters take three runs before Stuart Broad cuts it out. First runs of the morning for New Zealand.
Nicely bowled! On a length, drifts in, on fourth stump, it straightens a touch off the deck. Tom Blundell comes forward and tries to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge.

EDGED! It is a length ball, in the channel. Tom Blundell tries to block it away but gets a thick outside edge. Fortunately, he plays it with soft hands and the ball just lands short of Harry Brook in the slip cordon.
FOUR! This is a picturesque shot! Robinson pitches it up, outside off. Tom Blundell leans in and creams it through the cover region for a boundary.
Outside off, Tom Blundell leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, around off. Tom Blundell blocks it out watchfully. 10 runs off the first over. A positive start for the Kiwis.
This is flat, attaking the stumps. Tim Southee blocks it out firmly.

FOUR! Incredible effort from Ben Stokes. This could have been a stunning catch. Ben Stokes commits to this catch but it goes down in vain and to rub salt on the wounds, it rolls over the ropes. It is full and on off. Tim Southee dances down the track, gets under it and lofts it high towards long on. Ben Stokes runs backwards from mid on. He gives it a long chase, dives forward, although the ball does not stick in his palms and it goes for four.
Looped up, around off, Tim Southee blocks it out.
FOUR! Much better shot. No chance for any fielder this time. Tim Southee uses his feet, gets to the pitch of the ball and smacks it over the bowler's head for four runs.
A single now as this is tapped to point.
On  off, Tom Blundell eases it to the off side.

So close! It is much fuller, on fourth stump. Tim Southee tries to go downtown but misses it by a mile, although the ball whizzes past the off pole here. Tim Southee has some ladyluck on his side here.
Length and on off, blocked away.
FOUR! Tim Southee is scoring runs for fun here. It is a short ball, outside off. Tim Southee steps down and slaps it over covers for a cracking boundary.
Good length, wide of off. Tim Southee goes after it but misses.
Bit fuller, on off. Southee drives it to extra cover, but could not find the gap this time.

Ollie Robinson dishes a well-directed bouncer, on leg stump. Tim Southee goes back and tries to hook it away. He gets no connection here. The ball pings the helmet on its way to the keeper. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Floats it up, full and on off. Tom Blundell prods and blocks it into the deck.
Short, outside off. Tom Blundell cuts it hard to sweeper cover for one.
Tim Southee now rotates the striker as he nudges this full ball to the leg side. This is good running.
A bit short, turning away with some bounce. Tom Blundell goes back and punches it past extra covers for one more.
Full and on leg, defended out.
NO BALL! Jack Leach has to reload the final delivery. Full and on off, defended solidly.
On off, blocked to the off side.
Robinson goes full and on off. Blundell knocks it to covers.

Woah! Natural variation this time. It is a length ball, that nips in from outside off. Although it stays low off the deck. Tom Blundell gets beaten on the inside edge but is fortunate to see the ball go through to the keeper.
A single now as Tom Blundell punches this length ball to the off side.

Ollie Robinson fires it full, on middle and leg. Tim Southee shuffles and tries to flick it away. He gets some bat on it, although Ollie Robinson thinks it has hit his pads. Ben Stokes takes the review but the UltraEdge confirms that the bat is involved.
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Wonderful shot! It is pitched up, on fourth stump. Tom Blundell lunges and creams it through cover for four runs. He couldn't have hit it any better.
SIX! High and handsome! It is full, wide outside off. Tim Southee uses his feet and smokes it over the long on fence.
Shorter,outside off, turning away a bit. Tim Southee rocks back and tries to cut it away but misses. He gets beaten on the outside edge.

SIX! BANG! What a knock this is turning out to be from Tim Southee. He is certainly playing a captain's knock here. It is tossed up, full and on off. Tim Southee makes good use of the feet once again and dispatches it over the bowler's head for a biggie. He gets if half-ton in fine fashion. To be honest, Tim Southee is using his feet more than any top-orders for the Kiwis.
Full and on off, dabbed to the off side.

SIX! Tim Southee cannot do anything wrong with the bat this morning. It is looped up, outside off. Tim Southee gets down on one knee to smack it flat and hard over the long on fence. The umpire is being made to do some exercise in this over.
A single now as this full ball is tapped to the off side.
Length and on top of off. Tim Southee opens the face late and guides it to backward point.
A sharp bouncer, on the body. Tim Southee sways away from the line here.
SIX! Fireworks going on in Wellington. A short ball, on leg. Tim Southee swivels and hooks it over the square leg fence for a maximum.
Good length, sliding down leg. Tim Southee flicks it down to fine leg and crosses.
On a length, outside off, jags back in a touch. Tom Blundell makes a good leave.
Full, angled into the pads. Tom Blundell tucks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Up and over! It does not matter who comes into the attack. Tim Southee is speaking only one language here. It is a good-length ball, on middle. Tim Southee clears his front leg and slaps it over mid off for four runs.

DROPPED! And 200 up for New Zealand. It is a short ball, on off. Tim Southee tries to heave it across the line but it catches the top-edge. The ball goes way high in the air towards fine leg. Jack Leach gets to his right, settles under it but does not hold on to it. The batters take a couple.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tim Southee's entertaining innings comes to an end. It is full-length ball, on leg stump. Tim Southee goes for the flick but is a bit early into his shot. The ball takes the leading edge and lobs towards mid-wicket. Zak Crawley gets enough time to settle himself and takes a dolly here. New Zealand need 35 more runs to avoid follow-on.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Length ball, on the pads. Matt Henry flicks it to the leg side.
A bumper down leg, left alone.
Short one, on middle and leg. Matt Henry sways away from the line of the delivery here.
Fuller, in-line with the stumps. Tom Blundell steps down the wicket and blocks it solidly.
Short, outside off. Tom Blundell cuts it past backward point. He pushes hard for the first one and comes back for the second.
Leach drifts it in, around off. It turns away with some extra bounce. Tom Blundell gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to cut it away.
On off, tapped to the off side.
Flatter, outside off. Tom Blundell eases it to backward point.

Tom Blundell dances down the track to this full ball. He drills it back to the bowler. Jack Leach does well to make a half-stop and save a single here. An opportunity for England to attack the new batter in Henry.
FOUR! Matt Henry is off the mark with a boundary. It is a short ball, on off. Matt Henry gets inside the line and flicks it down to fine leg. A couple of bounces over the ropes.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Matt Henry tries to hook it away but misses.
On a length, outside off. Matt Henry upper cuts it down to third man and gets to the other end.
It is full, on fifth stump. Tom Blundell leans in and pushes it gently to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Tom Blundell holes out this time. It is a short ball, on off. Tom Blundell steps out of the crease and goes for the pull shot. He does not middle it and goes low and straight towards mid on. Jack Leach stationed there takes a sharp low catch by getting down on his knees.
Howout: c Jack Leach b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Length, on off. Neil Wagner blocks it to covers.
Full and on off. Henry drives it uppishly to the right of extra covers.
Fuller, on leg. Henry clips it through mid-wicket for one.
Floats it up, on off. blocked to point.
It is tossed up, around off. Neil Wagner goes for the reverse sweep but misses it completely. He wears it on his pads. Leach appeals but the umpire is unmoved.
On off, blocked on the front foot.
Flatter, outside off. Neil Wagner dabs it to the off side.
Back of a length and outside off, Matt Henry steers it towards point, Neil Wagner wants the run and is halfway down the pitch, but Henry is not interested.

OUT! TAKEN! Stuart Broad gets the last wicket! That is it for New Zealand ad they have been bowled out for 209. Broad lands this back of a length and on middle, angling in with extra bounce, Matt Henry gets hurried and is in a awkward position to defend, and the ball takes the outside edge and lobs up in the air towards gully where James Anderson takes a dolly.
Howout: c James Anderson b Stuart Broad

Commentary: James Anderson starts with a good-length delivery outside off, shaping furhter away, Tom Latham makes an easy leave.
Back of a length and outside off again, Tom Latham shoulders arms to it.

FOUR! Tom Latham and New Zealand are underway! James Anderson bowls this on a hard length but down the leg side, Tom Latham looks to flick it away, but gloves it just past the keeper where Ben Foakes dives to his right and the ball races towards the fine leg fence.
Short of a length and around off, Tom Latham offers no shot at it.
James Anderson goes a bit fuller and outside off, shaping away, Tom Latham moves across to play it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Pulls his length back now, on off, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Ollie Robinson begins with a wayward delivery down the leg side, Devon Conway leaves it alone and Ben Foakes dives to his right behind the stumps to make a good stop.
Ollie Robinson gets his length right this time around off, angling away, Devon Conway is beaten on the outiside edge as he tries to defend.
Back of a length and on middle, Devon Conway looks to play it, but misses due to the extra bounce and gets hit on his gloves.
On a length and on middle, Devon Conway leans on and blocks it awkwardly.
Fuller one and on off, Devon Conway keeps it out to the off side.
Full again but way outside off, Devon Conway did not bother to play at it.
This is on a good length and on off, shaping in, Tom Latham watches it through and defends it to the leg side.

Just short! This is on a good length again and around off, Tom Latham looks to block it, but gets an outside edge and the ball just falls short of slip cordon where the fielder dives to his right and parries it behind. Two runs taken!
Back of a length and on off, Tom Latham guides it towards point.
James Anderson bangs this short and on middle, Tom Latham pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket region with not much timing for a couple of runs.
Goes fuller and around off, shaping away, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Another full delivery outside off, Tom Latham decides playing against it.
This is pitched up and down the leg again, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Full and on middle, angling in, Devon Conway tries to block it, but gets an inside edge towards square leg. They cross.
Fuller again, on middle, swinging in sharply, Tom Latham misses his flick and gets hit on the pads as the ball rolls towards short leg.
Overpitched and on middle, Tom Latham tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and around leg, Tom Latham misses his flick again and the ball goes off his pads towards leg slip.
Goes fuller this time and outside off, shaping away, Tom Latham offers no shot at it.
Short of a length and on off, Devon Conway leaps up and dabs it to the left of gully.
This is on a good length and on off, swinging away, Devon Conway lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper.
Touch fuller and on off, shaping in, Devon Conway looks to fend it, but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Full again and on off, angling away, Devon Conway is a happy to leave it.
Back of a length and on off, Devon Conway guides it towards point.
A maiden over! This is on a hard length and on middle, Devon Conway blocks it down the pitch.
Edged but does not carry! This is full and on off, Tom Latham looks to push it away, but gets an outside edge which just falls short of second slip.
On a length and outside off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Fullish and on leg, Tom Latham misses his flick as the ball lobs up off his pads towards the keeper where Ben Foakes dives to his right to collect it.
Back of a length and in the channel outside off, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Good leave! This is on a good length and on off, nips back in, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper as the ball just goes past the off pole.
Short of a length and on middle, Tom Latham gets hurried with the bounce and nudges it with his gloves wide of short leg for a single.
FOUR! Good shot! James Anderson lands this short around the waist height, on middle, Tom Latham swivels and pulls it towards the deep square leg fence for a boundary.
Good comeback from James Anderson! He serves this on a good length and on the fifth stump line, nips away a bit, Tom Latham looks to block it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and on middle, angling in sharply, Tom Latham misses and gets hit high on his body.
Length again and on off, Tom Latham taps it in front of gully for a single.
Much fuller and outside off, angling away, Devon Conway tries to drive it, but misses it completely.
Back of a length and around off, Devon Conway offers no shot at it.
FOUR! Nice shot! Stuart Broad begins with a hafl-volley, on off, Tom Latham gets his front foot near the ball and drives it towards the wide long off fence for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, angling in, takes off after hitting the deck, Tom Latham looks to keep it down, but gets hit on the gloves due to the extra bounce.
Goes fuller and on off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Full again just outside off, shaping away, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Stuart Broad pitches it up, outside off, Tom Latham offers no shot at it.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham knocks it towards short covers and denies the single.
This is on a good length and on the fifth stump line, angling away, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and on middle and leg, Devon Conway turns it to he leg side.
Back of a length and around off, nips back in sharply, Devon Conway leaves it alone, but gets hit on his stomach area.
On a length and on off, Devon Conway tries to block it, but gets an outside edge on the bounce towards gully where the fielder dives to his left to stop it.
Touch fuller and on off, shaping in a bit, Devon Conway shoulders arms to it.
Fuller again and on off, angling away, Devon Conway once again is happy to let it go to the keeper. Another maiden over!
Full and on off, angling in, Tom Latham blocks it out.
On a length and outside off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Touch fuller and way outside off, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller again and outside off, swinging away, Tom Latham offers no shot at it.
Pulls his length back a bit. on off, angling in, Tom Latham fends it to the leg side.
Pitches this one up, on middle, Tom Latham blocks it back towards the bowler.
Anderson dishes a length ball, on leg stump. Conway stays inside the crease, closes the face of the bat and tucks it to the leg side.
This time Anderson goes full, outside off. angling across the left-hander. Devon Conway shoulders his arms at it.
Anderson now comes 'round the wicket and serves it on a length, on off stump. Conway shuffles and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
It is full, wide of off. Tom Latham leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, once again wide of off. Tom Latham isn't interested in playing away from his body here.
Three dots in a row to end the over! Anderson serves it full, on fourth stump. Tom Latham shuffles and blocks it to the leg side off the inner half.
Broad comes from 'round the wicket. He angles in a length ball, outside off. Conway gets forward to defend it out.
A length ball, angled in from outside off. Devon Conway is caught inside the crease here. He takes a blow near the box.
Full length, on sixth stump. Devon Conway blocks it to the leg side off the inner half.
This is much fuller, outside off. Devon Conway gets across and miscues his drive through covers. James Anderson gives it a long chase and keeps it down to three runs.
Length, outside off. Left alone by Latham.
On a length, on fifth stump, shaping further away. Tom Latham keeps his bat to himself.

Woah! Lands safely! Robinson hurls in a length ball, around middle. This one flies off the deck. Devon Conway tries to flick it through the leg side but gets pinged on his gloves. The ball pops up but lands wide of short leg. They take one.
Much fuller, on off. Latham dabs it to cover and takes a quick single.
Good-length ball, angling across the left-hander. Devon Conway is enticed into chasing after it but pulls his bat back in time.
Jaffa! Ollie Robinson dishes it bit fuller, on off, shapes away a touch. Devon Conway tries to block it away but does so inside the line.
A single now as this is worked to the off side.
Full length, on the pads. Tom Latham flicks it through square leg for a single.
Floats it up, outside off. It turns in off the deck. Tom Latham plays it with the turn and nudges it to the leg side.
Darted on the pads, Latham clips it behind square on the leg side. Not able to sneak it through the gap.
This is full, on leg. Latham tucks it past short leg.
Goes full, on off. Latham uses his feet and clips it to short mid-wicket.
Flatter one, angled into the pads. Tom Latham uses the depth of the crease, and flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.

EDGED! It is a loopy ball, around off, it grips and turns in. Devon Conway tries to defend it away but it catches the inside edge, on to the pads and falls safely on the leg side. Ollie Pope was standing behind rather than on the conventional short leg position. Conway could've been a goner.
Length and on off, defended out.
Good length, on middle, nips in a touch. Latham tries to flick it away but misses.
Ollie Robinson serves a length ball, on off. Latham gets it to the leg side off the inner half. One taken.
On a length, outside off. Conway leaves it alone for the keeper.
It is a length ball, sliding down leg. Devon Conway mistimes his flick through square leg for a single.
Tom Latham presses forward and defends this length ball watchfully.
It is tossed up, full and on off. Devon Conway defends it on his front foot.
Quicker and full, on the pads. Conway nudges it to the leg side.
Flatter, on the pads. Devon Conway goes back and clips it to square leg for one.
Once again, drifting down leg. Tom Latham tucks it behind square.
Too short, sliding down the leg side. Tom Latham hangs back and nudges it past short leg. They cross for one.
Darted on the pads, flicked to the leg side.
It is full, angled in on off. Latham drives it firmly towards mid off.
Ollie Robinson drifts in a length ball, outside off from 'round the wicket. The ball shapes further away after hitting the deck. Tom Latham does not bother.
Ollie Robinson now dishes a length ball, just outside off and it nips in a touch off the deck. Tom Latham trusts the bounce and makes a sharp leave.
Outside off, left alone.
It is full and on off. Tom Latham gets it to the left of backward point off the outer half.
A maiden for Ollie Robinson! Fuller, wide of off, it nips further away. Tom Latham lets it be.
Flatter, on the pads. Conway hangs back to flick it past the short leg fielder for a single.
Looped up, on middle and leg. Tom Latham now gets his wrist into play and takes a single.

The England fielders have their hands on their head here. It is much fuller, on middle. Devon Conway tries to flick it away but it catches the edge. The ball goes past Ben Stokes at leg slip. The batters take two.
A single now as this is tucked to mid-wicket.
Goes full and on off. Latham eases it to the off side for a single.
Loopy ball, on off, defended out solidly.
Too full and straight on the pads. Tom Latham clips it to deep square leg and collects a brace.
Length, wide of off. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
BEATEN! Ollie Robinson angles in a length ball, outside off. It straightens a touch off the deck. Tom Latham tries to have a poke at it but misses.
Full and on off. Tom Latham defends it to cover on his front foot.
Goes full, angled into the pads. Tom Latham goes for the flick but it rolls out to the left of the bowler off the outer half.
A loose delivery to end the over! It is a length ball, spilled down the leg side. Tom Latham does not go after it. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Leach starts with a full one, outside off. It turns in a long way. Conway gets an inside edge on his pads.
Floats it up, around off. It turns in with some extra bounce. The ball lobs off the inner half and evades short leg.
On off, defended out watchfully.
Darted on the pads, Conway flicks it to the leg side.
This is tossed up, on off. It flies off the deck. Devon Conway tries to defend it out on his front foot but misses. He takes a blow on his thigh pads.
On off, defended out solidly. A probing over from Leach comes to an end.
Stuart Broad begins with a full delivery, on middle, Tom Latham tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham blocks it down the pitch.
Goes a bit fuller and outside off, shaping away, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Overpitched and on middle, Tom Latham drives it back towards the bowler where Stuart Broad goes down and parries it towards mid on.
This is on a good length and on off, Tom Latham keeps it out to the off side.
Short of a length well outside off, Tom Latham shoulders arms to it.
Floated, short and on middle, Devon Conway moves back and fends it to the leg side.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Devon Conway blocks it out.
Flighted, full and on leg, Devon Conway nudges it towards square leg.
Flatter, short and on off, Devon Conway goes on his back foot and tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Quicker, full and on leg, Devon Conway turns it towards short mid-wicket again.
A single to end the over as this full delivery is driven down to long on by Conway.
FOUR! Nice shot! Stuart Broad serves this full and on off, swinging away a bit, Devon Conway leans on and drives it firmly and beats the extra covers fielder to collect a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, Devon Conway guides it with the outer half towards point.
Fuller one and outside off, shaping away, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
On a length and on middle, Devon Conway fends it to the right of short leg.
Length again and on middle, Devon Conway works it with the inner half wide of backward short leg where the fielder dives to his left to stop it.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Stuart Broad overpitches this one around off, Devon Conway once again drives it nicely wide of mid off where the fielder dives to his right but fails to stop it from going for a boundary.
Flighted and around middle, Tom Latham uses his feet and turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Short and on middle, Tom Latham moves back and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single. With that, the 50-runs partnership comes up between these two batters.
Flatter, full and on middle, Devon Conway works it towards long on for a run.
Slightly shorter and on leg, angling in, Tom Latham flicks it off the back foot wide of square leg for one.
Short again and on leg, Devon Conway nudges it straight to square leg.
Pushed through quicker, on off, Devon Conway defends it to the off side.
This is on a good length and outside off, Tom Latham is happy to let it go to the keeper.
Touch fuller and around off, Tom Latham leaves it alone again.
Full again and on off, shaping away, Tom Latham blocks it towards short covers.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham defends it to the off side.
BEAUTY! Stuart Broad serves this on a hard length and on the fifth stump line, shaping away, Tom Latham looks to play at it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Pitched up, on middle, Tom Latham clips it towards deep square leg for a single.
Flatter, short and on middle, Tom Latham moves back and tucks it straight towards short leg.
FOUR! Nice use of the feet! This is tossed up around middle, Tom Latham skips down the track and whips it towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Short and on middle, Tom Latham nudges it towards square leg.
Oh..that is close! This is flatter, full and on off, turning in sharply, Tom Latham goes for the cut, but misses as the ball goes past the inside edge towards the keeper.
Shortish and on middle, Tom Latham turns it towards short leg.
Floated, full and on leg, Tom Latham blocks it out.
This is on a good length around off, swinging away, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Back of a length and outside off, Devon Conway lifts his bat and lets it go to the keeper, but is surprised by the extra bounce generated.
Short of a length and on off, angling in, Devon Conway tries to fend it, but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Short of a length again and on off, Devon Conway steers it towards gully.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Conway! This is too full from Broad, on middle and leg, Devon Conway stays there and clips it towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Fuller once more, on off, Devon Conway blocks it out towards short covers.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Tom Latham tucks it wide of short mid-wicket for a single.
Floated, full and on off, Devon Conway defends it on the front foot.
Slightly shorter and on off, Devon Conway moves back and works it to the left of short mid-wicket.
On middle, blocked out.
Flighted, full and around off, Devon Conway strides out and defends off the inner half to the leg side.
Quicker, full and on off, Devon Conway is solid in his defense again.
Fuller one but down the leg side, Tom Latham misses his flick and Ben Foakes gathers it behind the stumps moving to his right.
Back of a length and on off, Tom Latham punches it through covers and comes back for the second.
On a length but around leg again, Tom Latham lets it go to the keeper.
Stuart Broad bangs this short and on middle, Tom Latham pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.
Short and on middle, Devon Conway swivels and pulls it straight to square leg.
Back of a length and on off, Devon Conway taps it to the off side for one.
SIX! BANG! Devon Conway goes big now! This is tossed up around middle, Devon Conway skips down the track and smokes it over the wide long on fence for a biggie.
Floated, full and on off, Devon Conway leans on and blocks it out.
Flatter, full and around off, Devon Conway defends it on the front foot.
On off, kept out.
FOUR! Fine shot! Jack Leach lands this a bit short and on off, Devon Conway quickly moves back and punches it through extra covers for a boundary.
Slower through the air, on off, turning in, Devon Conway strides out to defend, but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a stiffled appeal for LBW, but nothing doing for the umpire.
Length ball, sliding down leg. Latham tucks it through square leg and crosses.
It is a much fuller this time, on off. It is nips in off the deck. Conway gets an inside edge on his pads. There is appeal for lbw but the umpire shakes his head.
Length and on off, defended out.

FOUR! Edgy! James Anderson serves a length ball, around off, angling across. Devon Conway tries to poke it out but only manages to get a thick outside edge.The ball goes past Zak Crawley at third slip and runs down to third man.
Length, on off, defended out.
Beaten! Good length, outside off, shaping further away. Devon Conway tries to go after it but misses.
Shorter, into the body. Latham goes back and tucks it behind square on the leg side.
On off, defended to the left of the bowler.
Floats it up, on off. Latham uses his feet and clips it to short mid on.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Once again Leach attacks around the leg stump. Latham tucks it to square leg.
Tom Latham gets to the pitch of this ball and flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Anderson hurls a length ball, around off. It gets some extra bounce off the deck. Devon Conway blocks it from his crease.
Full, sliding down leg, flicked to mid-wicket.
Anderson angles this one across the left-hander on a fuller length. Conway blocks it to the off side.
Length, on the pads. Conway closes the face and works it to the on side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Devon Conway clips it to mid-wicket.
Good length, on top of off. Conway goes back and dabs it into the wicket.
Shorter, in the channel. Latham stays back and flicks it to mid-wicket.
A single now as this is nudged towards square leg.
Flatter, outside off, defended back to the bowler.
Devon Conway comes down the track to this full one, on off. Conway flicks it to deep square leg for a brace.
On off, blocked out.
Goes full and outside off. Devon Conway prods and smothers it away.
FOUR! Top shot! It is a short ball, wide of off. Tom Latham stays back and crunches it through point. Ben Stokes gives it a chase but the ball has enough legs to reach the fence.
On off, defended out.
It is a length ball, on fourth stump, shapes away a bit. Latham angles his blade down. The ball takes the outside edge but meets Ollie Pope at slip cordon on a bounce.
Full and on off, blocked out watchfully.
Darted on the pads, Tom Latham flicks it to the leg side for one. He records 5000 Test runs for New Zealand.
This is outside off, left alone.
Looped up, on off. Tom Latham lunges and blocks.
Shorter, on leg stump. Latham nudges it to the leg side.
Tom Latham gets down the track to this full one and flicks it to square leg.
LEG BYE! This is floated, on the pads. Latham misses his flick. The ball goes to fine leg off the pads. They cross for one leg bye.
On middle and leg, defended to the leg side.
Angled into the pads on a fuller length, Conway clips it through square leg and takes a single.
Devon Conway stays back to defend this good-length ball.
A length ball, in the channel. Devon Conway makes a sharp leave.
Fuller, wide outside off, shaping further away. Left alone.
Length, angled across the left-hander. Devon Conway steps across and shoulders his arms at it.
Good length, sliding down leg. Devon Conway tries to flick it away but misses. It brushes his thigh pads and runs down to fine leg. They collect two leg byes.
Anderson fires in a length ball, around middle and leg. Devon Conway gets beaten and takes a blow high on his pads.
Spin straightaway. Flighted and full, wide of off, turning away sharply. Tom Latham lets it be.
Tossed up, on off, defended back to the bowler off the toe-end.
It is looped up, outside off, it grips and turns away. Left alone.
Shorter, on off. Latham goes back and slaps it hard to long on for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up, outside off, left alone once again.
Fraction short, outside off. Tom Latham cuts it towards backward point but could not find the gap.
On off, defeded out watchfully.
Anderson serves a length ball, on fourth stump. Latham gets it to the right of backward point off the outer half. One taken.
FOUR! Good shot. Back of a length, outside off. Devon Conway pulls it along the ground through covers for four runs.
This is on a length, wide of off. Defended out watchfully.
Good length, in the channel. Devon Conway tries to have a poke at it but gets beaten in the process.
Floats it up, outside off. Tom Latham has no shot to offer.
Incredible innings! 100 up on the board for New Zealand. It is short and outside off. Latham cuts it hard to sweeper cover for one.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Loopy ball, outside off, spinning away. Devon Conway lets it be.
Once again, flighted one, outside off. Devon Conway makes a leave.
Full and on off, Devon Conway lunges and defends it into the deck.
FIFTY FOR LATHAM! This has been a fine knock from him and he will look to make this big now. Ollie Robinson bowls this full and on middle, Tom Latham flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
EDGED AND FOUR! This is on a good length and around off, Tom Latham looks to play at it, but gets an outisde edge on the bounce and past slip cordon for a boundary.
FOUR! Great shot! Ollie Robinson lands this short and on middle, Tom Latham picks up the length early and pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Goes fuller this time, on middle, Tom Latham blocks it out.
Full again and on off, Tom Latham keeps it out to the off side.
On a length and on off, Tom Latham is two minds and decide to leave it in the end, but is a bit late to withdraw his bat and gets a bottom edge onto the pitch.
Tossed up, full and on off, turning away, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Floated, full and on middle, Devon Conway blocks it out.
Flighted, full and on off turning away again, Devon Conway let it be.
FIFTY FOR CONWAY! Both the openers get to fifties and New Zealand will be hoping that they take this gane deep now. This is short and on off, Devon Conway pushes it wide of short covers for one.
FOUR! Through the gap! This is flatter and outside off, Tom Latham moves back and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Looped up, full and on off, Tom Latham blocks it out.
Fuller one and on off, Devon Conway keeps it out to the off side.
On a length and on middle, Devon Conway turns it to the leg side.
Length again and on off, Devon Conway defends it towards short covers.
Pitched up, on off, Devon Conway blocks it on the front foot.
Ollie Robinson continues with the fuller length and outside off, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Pulls his length back a bit, on off, Devon Conway negotiates it well.
Tossed up around off, Tom Latham uses his feet to block it out.
Floated, short and on middle, turning in, Tom Latham moves back and keeps it down just past backward short leg.
Flatter, short and on off, Tom Latham looks to cut it, but bunts it onto the pitch.
On middle, blocked out.
Quicker, short and on off, Tom Latham defends it on the back foot.

Dropped! A very tough chance though. This is flighted and on off, Tom Latham uses his feet and thrashes it uppishly towards the bowler where Jack Leach goes down but fails to grab on and only makes a half-stop. They cross.
FOUR! Nice shot! Ollie Robinson bangs in a bouncer around leg, Tom Latham hooks it wide of third man for a boundary.
Back of a length and around off, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
On a length and on mddle, Tom Latham nudges it through square leg for a single.
Close! This si full and around off, angling away, Devon Conway goes for the big booming drive, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length and on off, Devon Conway leaves it alone.
Length again and down the leg, Devon Conway lets it go to the keeper.
Quicker, full and well outside off, Tom Latham moves across and leaves it alone.
Floated, short and on off, turning in, Tom Latham leans on to defend, but keeps it down with the gloves due to the extra bounce.
Tossed up, full and on middle Tom Latham blocks it out.
Slower through the air, on off, turning in. Tom Latham goes down for a sweep, but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Floated, full and on off, Tom Latham uses his feet to defend, but gets an outside edge.
FOUR! Fine shot! This is short and on middle, Tom Latham moves back quickly and pulls it towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Devon Conway drives it towards short covers where the fielder dives to his left to stop it.
Quicker, full and on off, Devon Conway knocks it towards mid off.
Flighted, full and on off, Devon Conway keeps it out to the off side.
Flatter, full and on off, Devon Conway drills it towards sweeper covers for one.
A bit short and on off, Tom Latham is solid in his defense.
Flighted, full and outside off, turning away, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Tossed up, full and on off, Devon Conway leans on and blocks it out.
Short and on off, Devon Conway pushes it towards short covers.
Short again and on middle, Devon Conway punches it off the back foot towards long on for a single.
Quicker, full and on middle, Tom Latham tucks it a bit uppishly towards short leg where Ollie Pope reacts well and stops it diving to his right.
On middle, blocked out.
Flatter, full and on off, Tom Latham defends it on the front foot.
Tossed up, full and on off, Devon Conway leans on and blocks it out.
On middle, blocked out.
Flighted, full and on off, Devon Conway goes for the drive where the ball deflects off the toes of silly point towarrds sweeper covers. They cross.
Tossed up, short and on off, turning away, Tom Latham leaves it alone.
Quicker and outside off, turning away again, Tom Latham offers no shot at it.
A dot to end the over! This is darted in full and on middle, Tom Latham keeps it out well. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3!
WIDE! Ben Stokes starts with a sharp bouncer, on leg. This one goes way over the batter's head. The umpire signals a wide.
A bouncer once again, on leg stump. Devon Conway ducks under it.
NO BALL! Ben Stokes bends his back hard once again and serves a well-directed short ball, on leg stump. Devon Conway lets it be.
Back of a length, down the leg side. Conway swivels and pulls it down to fine leg. One taken.

NO BALL! A mini-game going on between the umpire and Stokes now. Ben Stokes persists with the short balls. He dishes one once again. The umpire is not happy and signals a no ball, as he has been given fair amount of warnings.
Length ball, on fourth stump. Latham punches it to cover. The fielder makes a half-stop by diving to his left. One taken.
Devon Conway gets on his front foot and defends it to the off side.
Full length, outside off. Conway leans in and drives it towards covers. Once again the fielder kills the pace by getting a hand on it. The batter cross for one.
Length and on off, defended to mid off.
Flighted, on middle and leg. Conway hangs back and clips it past Pope at short leg. The batters take three runs before the fielder cuts it off.
Much quicker and full, sliding down leg. Latham goes back and nudges it in front of short leg.
A single now as this full ball is knocked down the park to long on.
Full and on off, defended into the turf.
Length and on the pads. Conway goes back and tucks it to the leg side. Ollie Pope stops it with his legs.
Flatter and on off, tapped to point.
Ben Stokes starts this over with a short one as well. The umpire signals first one of the over. It is a bouncer, on off. Tom Latham ducks under it.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Back of a length, wide outside off. Tom Latham rides the bounce and cuts it hard through point for four runs.
Good length, sliding down leg. Tom Latham flicks it to fine leg and crosses.
A length ball, going down leg. Conway shows no interest in chasing this one.

Short ball, around the hips. Devon Conway swivels and pulls it along the ground behind square on the leg side. Ben Duckett comes across from fine leg and saves a certain boundary this time with a dive. Two taken.
NO BALL! Short and on middle. Conway pulls it to deep square leg for one. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
Back of a length, angled down leg. Latham pulls it down to fine leg and crosses.
A bit short, on fourth stump. Latham goes back and tucks it to short leg.
Short again, on off. Latham clips it through square leg for a single.
Floats it up, full and outside off. Devon Conway steps across and pads it out.
Much fuller, on off. Conway blocks it out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Once again it is the combination of Jack Leach and Ollie Pope that bring success to this England side. It is tossed up, around off. It grips and turns in a touch with some extra bounce. Devon Conway gets on his front foot and tries to defend it out. The ball though pops up off the inside edge. Ollie Pope dives forward and pouches the ball safely with both hands. Devon Conway is gutted as he walks off the field here.
Howout: c Ollie Pope b Jack Leach

Commentary: Jack Leach almost got his second wicket here. It is flighted full and outside off. Kane Williamson gets on his front foot to block it away. The ball holds in the wicket a bit and it comes off the top half of the blade. It fortunately evades the out stretched hand of Ollie Pope at silly point.
Broad starts with a length ball, sliding down leg. Latham lets it go.
Back of a length, sliding down leg. Tom Latham swivels and pulls it to deep square leg for a single. A round of applause now from the crowd as 150 comes up for the Kiwis.
A length ball, angled into the pads. Kane Williamson stays back and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone by the former New Zealand skipper.
Length and on off, blocked out.
Short one, on off. Kane Williamson pulls it down to square leg for two runs.
Darted on the pads, Latham clips it past square leg for one.
Full and on off, defended on the front foot.
On the pads, flicked to the leg side.
This is full, attacking the stumps. Kane Williamson defends it back to the bowler.
Flights it up, full and outside off. Kane Williamson smothers it on his front foot.
Full, on leg. Kane Williamson clips it to the right of mid on and crosses.
Floated, short and on middle, Kane Williamson moves back and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Quicker, short and on off, Tom Latham turns it towards short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on off, Tom Latham blocks it towards short covers.
Flighted and around middle, Tom Latham makes it a low full toss and drills it towards mid on.

OUT! LBW! Joe Root strikes! Tom Latham falls but this time playing the traditional sweep. Root floats this one up, full and on off, Tom Latham goes down and tries to sweep, but misses and gets rapped around his pads. There is a huge appeal for LBW, and up goes the fineger. Tom Latham takes the review though. UltraEdge shows no bat involded and Ball Tracking indicates impact is umpire's call. Tom Latham will have to go back to the hut after playing a fine knock.
Howout: lbw b Joe Root

Commentary: Looped up, full and on off, Will Young drives it towards short covers.
Full and on off, Will Young blocks it to the off side.
This is on a good length and outside off, Will Young leaves it alone.
Pitched up, on off, Will Young knocks it towards mid off.
Overpitched and on middle, Will Young clips it towards the vacant deep mid-wicket region for three runs.
On a length and on off, angling in, Kane Williamson lets it go to the keeper.
Goes fuller and around leg, Kane Williamson works it towards short mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on off, Will Young defends it with the outer half towards backward point.
Floated, full and on leg, Will Young turns it towards short leg region.
Flighted, full and on middle, Will Young blocks it down the pitch.
Flatter, full and on leg, Will Young keeps it out to the leg side.
A bit short and on leg, Will Young moves back and nudges it towards short fine leg.
A maiden over! This is looped up, full and on middle, Will Young is solid in his defense again.
Full and on off, Kane Williamson defends it towards point.
This is on a good length and in the channel outside off, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
FOUR! Good shot! Stuart Broad lands this short and on middle, Kane Williamson picks up the length early and pulls it in front of the square on the leg side for a boudnary.
On a length and on middle, Kane Williamson knocks it back towards the bowler.
Back of a length and around off, shaping away, Kane Williamson offers no shot at it.
Length again and on off, Kane Williamson looks to play at it, but gets beaten on the outside edge due to the away movement.
Tossed up, full and on off, Will Young drives it straight into the foot of silly point.
Floated, full and on off, Will Young guides it towards point.
Flighted, full and on off, Will Young pushes it towards point again.
Slightly shorter and on middle, turning away, Will Young decides late to leave it, but gets an outside edge on the bounce towards point.
Short again and on off, Will Young moves back and punches it towards sweeper covers for a single.
Slower through the air, on middle, angling in, grips and turns away, Kane Williamson gets beaten on the outside edge as he tries to defend.
Fuller in length and on off, Will Young defends it to the off side.
Full again and on off, Will Young keeps it out to the left of the bowler.
Overpitched and on middle, Will Young clips it wide of mid-wicket and collects three runs as the fielder chases it down.
James Anderson continues with his fuller length, on off, Kane Williamson negotiates it well again.
Another pitched-up delivery, on off, Kane Williamson knocks it towards point.
Short of a length and around off, Kane Williamson leaves it alone.
Tosses it up, on off. Young prods and blocks it to the off side.
Flighted and on off, blocked to silly point.
Shorter, on fourth stump. Young punches it to point.

OUT! TIMBER! Absolute peach of a delivery. Will Young is undone here. Jack Leach picks up his second wicket. Leach angles it in, full and on middle. The ball grips and turns away sharply. Will Young goes back inside the crease and tries to block it out, although he does so inside the line. The ball goes sneaks past the outside edge and hits the top of off.
Howout: b Jack Leach

Commentary: Full and outside off. Henry Nicholls gets it to short leg off the inner half.
Flatter and on middle. Henry Nicholls uses the depth of the crease and tucks it to the leg side. A wicket-maiden for Jack Leach. New Zealand now trail by 59 runs.
Good length, on top of off. Kane Williamson stays back and clips it towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, on a length. Kane Williamson shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, angled in on off. Kane Williamson uses the depth of the crease and tucks it to the leg side.
This is a length delivery, outside off. Kane Williamson leaves it alone for the keeper.
Much fuller, on off. Kane Williamson presses forward and blocks it to the off side off the bottom half.
Length, on the pads. Kane Williamson flicks it down to fine leg and crosses.
Floated and full, outside off. Kane Williamson prods and fends it out.
Loopy ball, on off. Kane Williamson gets forward and dabs it into the wicket.
Short one, wide of off. Kane Williamson cuts it to deep point. There is a misfield and they collect a brace.
Slower through the air, outside off. Kane Williamson blocks it out to safety.
Much fuller, in-line with the stumps. Kane Williamson prods and blocks it with full face.
Fuller, sliding down leg. Kane Williamson eases it to the leg side.
It is much fuller, outside off, angled across. Henry Nicholls makes a good leave.
Full length, on off. Henry Nicholls shuffles and clips it through mid-wicket for a single. He gets off the mark now.
FOUR! Nicely played! Anderson hurls in a length ball, sliding down leg. Kane Williamson tickles it down to fine leg for four runs.
Fraction short, outside off. Kane Williamson lets it be.
Much fuller this time, on off. Kane Williamson steps across and dabs it out to covers.
Kane Williamson drives this full ball gently back towards the bowler.
Floats it up, outside off. Henry Nicholls steps outside the line and wears a blow on his pads.
Henry Nicholls stands tall and knocks this flatter ball towards mid on.
It is a full ball. Henry Nicholls gets low and sweeps this from outside off to deep square leg for just a single.
On the pads, clipped to the on side for one more.
Slower one, on off. Henry Nicholls defends it with soft hands.
This one lands around off and turns in sharply off the deck with some extra bounce, Henry Nicholls goes back and flicks it to square leg.
This is on a good length and on middle, Kane Williamson nudges it towards square leg.
James Anderson bowls this on a hard length and around off, Kane Williamson withdraws his bat at the last moment and leaves it alone.
Goes fuller this time, on off, Kane Williamson blocks it towards short covers.
Full again and on off, Kane Williamson pats it onto the ground on the off side.
Overpitched and on middle, Kane Williamson turns it towards short mid-wicket.
On a length and on off, Kane Williamson keeps it out again.
Floated, short and on off, Henry Nicholls tucks it past short leg.
Tossed up, full and on off, Henry Nicholls fends it towards short mid-wicket.
Short and on middle, Henry Nicholls thinks about the sweep at first, but adjusts well and flicks it off the back foot wide of square leg for a brace.
Slower through the air, on off, turning in, Henry Nicholls watches it through and keeps it out.
Flatter, full and on middle, Henry Nicholls looks to blocks it, but gets an inside edge just past short leg.
A bit short and on middle, Henry Nicholls moves back and knocks it towards mid on.
Full and on off, Kane Williamson keeps it out to the off side.
Full again and on middle, Kane Williamson tucks it towards wide of mid on for a single.
On a length and on off, Henry Nicholls pushes it towards short covers.
Back of a length and outside off, angling away, Henry Nicholls slashes at it, but misses. He does not need to play at these.
Touch fuller and on off, shaping away, Henry Nicholls shoudlers arms to it.
Fuller once more and on off, angling away, Henry Nicholls lets it go to the keeper.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Kane Williamson turns it to the leg side.
Floated, full and on middle, Kane Williamson prods forward and blocks it out.
A bit short and on middle, Kane Williamson flicks it off the back foot towards deep square leg for a single.

Dropped! A great effort though! This is flighted, full and on middle, Henry Nicholls leans on to defend, but does so with the inner half and uppishly towards short leg where Ollie Pope goes down on his right, but fails to grab it low.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Henry Nicholls defends it on the front foot.
Shortish and on middle, Henry Nicholls moves back and forces it towards long on for a run.
Good-length ball, angled across, in the channel. Henry Nicholls shuffles and dabs it to point.
Fuller, on fifth stump. Henry Nicholls makes a good leave here.
Ollie Robinson once again serves a full-length ball, outside off. Henry Nicholls has no shot to offer.
It is a sharp bouncer, on off. Henry Nicholls ducks under it.
Robinson dishes it full, and around off. This one spits off the deck. It flies off the inner half towards mid-wicket but lands safely. One taken.
Length and on off, defended out solidly.
Floated and full, around off. Henry Nicholls gets behind the line and defends it out.
This one turns in from outside off. Henry Nicholls goes back and nudges it to the leg side.
Henry Nicholls steps down the wicket and dabs it down into the wicket.
Tosses it up, outside off, turning in. Henry Nicholls blocks it watchfully.
Full and on off, worked to the left of the bowler.
Flighted and full, on fifth stump. Henry Nicholls lunges forward and smothers it out. Jack Leach records his fifth maiden of the innings.
It is a length ball that nips in from outside off. Kane Williamson defends it off the bottom half of the blade. It fortunately sneaks past the stumps and goes to fine leg for a single.
A sharp bumper, on middle. Henry Nicholls ducks under it.
Ollie Robinson bends his back hard and dishes a short ball, on off. Henry Nicholls swivels and tries to go for the hook shot but he does not connect.
Ollie Robinson serves it full, on fourth stump. It flies off the deck. Henry Nicholls makes a good leave.
Full length, around off. Henry Nicholls gets on his front foot and gets it to the leg side off the inner half.
A length ball, angled across, outside off. Henry Nicholls pushes it gently through covers for a single.
Henry Nicholls gets down on one knee and sweeps this full ball to deep square leg from outside off. They take a single.
It comes in with the arm, full and on middle. Kane Williamson blocks it with full face.
Kane Williamson lunges forward to this full ball and blocks it back to the bowler.
Goes full, sliding down leg. Kane Williamson tucks it to the leg side.
It is full, angled into the pads. Kane Williamson nudges it through mid-wicket for a single.
A single now as this full delivery is clipped towards mid-wicket.
It is full, sliding down leg. Henry Nicholls prods and sweeps it down to square leg for a brace.
Tosses it up, around off. Henry Nicholls tries to defend it out but it flies off the outside edge. It does not carry to Ben Stokes.
On off, defended out.
Floated and full, on off. Henry Nicholls paddles it towards fine leg. Ben Foakes though shows quick reflexs and gathers the ball.
Full, on leg. Henry Nicholls flicks it through mid-wicket for two runs.
Joe Root serves it full, on middle and leg. Henry Nicholls tucks it to the on side and gets to the other end.
Floated, short and on middle, Henry Nicholls knocks it towards mid on.
Tossed up, full and on off, Henry Nicholls looks to sweep it, but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW, but turned down.
Flatter, short and on middle, Henry Nicholls nudges it towards backward square leg.
Shortish and on middle, Henry Nicholls defends it off the back foot.
Quicker, short and on middle, turning in, Henry Nicholls moves back and keeps it out.
Flighted, full and on off, Henry Nicholls mistimes his sweep towards short leg.

A huge appeal for caught behind, but the finger stays down. Ben Stokes decides to take the review. Joe Root lands this short and on off, turning in, Kane Williamson lets it go, but the ball brushes off his arm guard and goes towards the keeper where Ben Foakes pouches it. UltraEdge confirms the same and the on-field decision of Not Out remains.
Tossed up, full and on off, Kane Williamson drives it towards short covers.
Floated, full and on middle, Kane Williamson leans on and blocks it out.
Flatter, full and on middle, Kane Williamson keeps it out onto the pitch.
Shorter in length and on off, Kane Williamson cuts it wide of covers for a single.
Flighted, full and on middle, Henry Nicholls prods forward and defends it.
Flighted, full and on middle, Kane Williamson blocks it back to the bowler.
Floated, full and on middle, Kane Williamson defends it past silly point.
A bit short and on middle, Kane Williamson moves back and pushes it towards mid on.
Gives this one some air, on off, Kane Williamson keeps it out to the right of second slip.
Flatter, short and outside off, Kane Williamson punches it towards sweeper covers for a single.
Quicker, full and on off, Henry Nicholls turns it to the right of short leg.
Tossed up, full and on off, Kane Williamson leans on and blocks it out.
Short and on middle, Kane Williamson taps it towards short leg.
Floated, full and on off, Kane Williamson pushes it towards short covers.
Flighted, full and on leg, Kane Williamson tucks it towards short leg.

Back of a length drifting down leg, James Anderson looks to flick this towards fine leg but gets a faint edge and Tom Blundell dives to his right and collects the most important catch of the match.
